29 void cart2geo(
30  double *x,
31  double *z,
32  double *lon,
33  double *lat) {
34 
35  double radius = NORM(x);
36  *lat = asin(x[2] / radius) * 180. / M_PI;
37  *lon = atan2(x[1], x[0]) * 180. / M_PI;
38  *z = radius - RE;
39 }
40

291 #ifdef _OPENACC
292 #pragma acc declare copyin(clim_hno3_var)
293 #endif
294 
295 double clim_hno3(
296  double t,
297  double lat,
298  double p) {
299 
300  /* Get seconds since begin of year... */
301  double sec = FMOD(t, 365.25 * 86400.);
302  while (sec < 0)
303  sec += 365.25 * 86400.;
304 
305  /* Check pressure... */
306  if (p < clim_hno3_ps[0])
307  p = clim_hno3_ps[0];
308  else if (p > clim_hno3_ps[9])
309  p = clim_hno3_ps[9];
310 
311  /* Check latitude... */
312  if (lat < clim_hno3_lats[0])
313  lat = clim_hno3_lats[0];
314  else if (lat > clim_hno3_lats[17])
315  lat = clim_hno3_lats[17];
316 
317  /* Get indices... */
318  int isec = locate_irr(clim_hno3_secs, 12, sec);
319  int ilat = locate_reg(clim_hno3_lats, 18, lat);
320  int ip = locate_irr(clim_hno3_ps, 10, p);
321 
322  /* Interpolate HNO3 climatology (Froidevaux et al., 2015)... */
323  double aux00 = LIN(clim_hno3_ps[ip],
324  clim_hno3_var[isec][ilat][ip],
325  clim_hno3_ps[ip + 1],
326  clim_hno3_var[isec][ilat][ip + 1], p);
327  double aux01 = LIN(clim_hno3_ps[ip],
328  clim_hno3_var[isec][ilat + 1][ip],
329  clim_hno3_ps[ip + 1],
330  clim_hno3_var[isec][ilat + 1][ip + 1], p);
331  double aux10 = LIN(clim_hno3_ps[ip],
332  clim_hno3_var[isec + 1][ilat][ip],
333  clim_hno3_ps[ip + 1],
334  clim_hno3_var[isec + 1][ilat][ip + 1], p);
335  double aux11 = LIN(clim_hno3_ps[ip],
336  clim_hno3_var[isec + 1][ilat + 1][ip],
337  clim_hno3_ps[ip + 1],
338  clim_hno3_var[isec + 1][ilat + 1][ip + 1], p);
339  aux00 = LIN(clim_hno3_lats[ilat], aux00,
340  clim_hno3_lats[ilat + 1], aux01, lat);
341  aux11 = LIN(clim_hno3_lats[ilat], aux10,
342  clim_hno3_lats[ilat + 1], aux11, lat);
343  aux00 = LIN(clim_hno3_secs[isec], aux00,
344  clim_hno3_secs[isec + 1], aux11, sec);
345  return GSL_MAX(aux00, 0.0);
346 }
347

1325 #ifdef _OPENACC
1326 #pragma acc declare copyin(clim_oh_var)
1327 #endif
1328 
1329 double clim_oh(
1330  double t,
1331  double lat,
1332  double p) {
1333 
1334  /* Get seconds since begin of year... */
1335  double sec = FMOD(t, 365.25 * 86400.);
1336  while (sec < 0)
1337  sec += 365.25 * 86400.;
1338 
1339  /* Check pressure... */
1340  if (p < clim_oh_ps[0])
1341  p = clim_oh_ps[0];
1342  else if (p > clim_oh_ps[33])
1343  p = clim_oh_ps[33];
1344 
1345  /* Check latitude... */
1346  if (lat < clim_oh_lats[0])
1347  lat = clim_oh_lats[0];
1348  else if (lat > clim_oh_lats[17])
1349  lat = clim_oh_lats[17];
1350 
1351  /* Get indices... */
1352  int isec = locate_irr(clim_oh_secs, 12, sec);
1353  int ilat = locate_reg(clim_oh_lats, 18, lat);
1354  int ip = locate_irr(clim_oh_ps, 34, p);
1355 
1356  /* Interpolate OH climatology (Pommrich et al., 2014)... */
1357  double aux00 = LIN(clim_oh_ps[ip],
1358  clim_oh_var[isec][ilat][ip],
1359  clim_oh_ps[ip + 1],
1360  clim_oh_var[isec][ilat][ip + 1], p);
1361  double aux01 = LIN(clim_oh_ps[ip],
1362  clim_oh_var[isec][ilat + 1][ip],
1363  clim_oh_ps[ip + 1],
1364  clim_oh_var[isec][ilat + 1][ip + 1], p);
1365  double aux10 = LIN(clim_oh_ps[ip],
1366  clim_oh_var[isec + 1][ilat][ip],
1367  clim_oh_ps[ip + 1],
1368  clim_oh_var[isec + 1][ilat][ip + 1], p);
1369  double aux11 = LIN(clim_oh_ps[ip],
1370  clim_oh_var[isec + 1][ilat + 1][ip],
1371  clim_oh_ps[ip + 1],
1372  clim_oh_var[isec + 1][ilat + 1][ip + 1], p);
1373  aux00 = LIN(clim_oh_lats[ilat], aux00, clim_oh_lats[ilat + 1], aux01, lat);
1374  aux11 = LIN(clim_oh_lats[ilat], aux10, clim_oh_lats[ilat + 1], aux11, lat);
1375  aux00 = LIN(clim_oh_secs[isec], aux00, clim_oh_secs[isec + 1], aux11, sec);
1376  return GSL_MAX(1e6 * aux00, 0.0);
1377 }

1506 #ifdef _OPENACC
1507 #pragma acc declare copyin(clim_tropo_tps)
1508 #endif
1509 
1510 double clim_tropo(
1511  double t,
1512  double lat) {
1513 
1514  /* Get seconds since begin of year... */
1515  double sec = FMOD(t, 365.25 * 86400.);
1516  while (sec < 0)
1517  sec += 365.25 * 86400.;
1518 
1519  /* Get indices... */
1520  int isec = locate_irr(clim_tropo_secs, 12, sec);
1521  int ilat = locate_reg(clim_tropo_lats, 73, lat);
1522 
1523  /* Interpolate tropopause data (NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis 1)... */
1524  double p0 = LIN(clim_tropo_lats[ilat],
1525  clim_tropo_tps[isec][ilat],
1526  clim_tropo_lats[ilat + 1],
1527  clim_tropo_tps[isec][ilat + 1], lat);
1528  double p1 = LIN(clim_tropo_lats[ilat],
1529  clim_tropo_tps[isec + 1][ilat],
1530  clim_tropo_lats[ilat + 1],
1531  clim_tropo_tps[isec + 1][ilat + 1], lat);
1532  return LIN(clim_tropo_secs[isec], p0, clim_tropo_secs[isec + 1], p1, sec);
1533 }
1534 
1535 /*****************************************************************************/
1536 
1537 void day2doy(
1538  int year,
1539  int mon,
1540  int day,
1541  int *doy) {
1542 
1543  int d0[12] = { 1, 32, 60, 91, 121, 152, 182, 213, 244, 274, 305, 335 };
1544  int d0l[12] = { 1, 32, 61, 92, 122, 153, 183, 214, 245, 275, 306, 336 };
1545 
1546  /* Get day of year... */
1547  if (year % 400 == 0 || (year % 100 != 0 && year % 4 == 0))
1548  *doy = d0l[mon - 1] + day - 1;
1549  else
1550  *doy = d0[mon - 1] + day - 1;
1551 }
1552 
1553 /*****************************************************************************/
1554 
1555 void doy2day(
1556  int year,
1557  int doy,
1558  int *mon,
1559  int *day) {
1560 
1561  int d0[12] = { 1, 32, 60, 91, 121, 152, 182, 213, 244, 274, 305, 335 };
1562  int d0l[12] = { 1, 32, 61, 92, 122, 153, 183, 214, 245, 275, 306, 336 };
1563  int i;
1564 
1565  /* Get month and day... */
1566  if (year % 400 == 0 || (year % 100 != 0 && year % 4 == 0)) {
1567  for (i = 11; i >= 0; i--)
1568  if (d0l[i] <= doy)
1569  break;
1570  *mon = i + 1;
1571  *day = doy - d0l[i] + 1;
1572  } else {
1573  for (i = 11; i >= 0; i--)
1574  if (d0[i] <= doy)
1575  break;
1576  *mon = i + 1;
1577  *day = doy - d0[i] + 1;
1578  }
1579 }
1580 
1581 /*****************************************************************************/
1582 
1583 void geo2cart(
1584  double z,
1585  double lon,
1586  double lat,
1587  double *x) {
1588 
1589  double radius = z + RE;
1590  x[0] = radius * cos(lat / 180. * M_PI) * cos(lon / 180. * M_PI);
1591  x[1] = radius * cos(lat / 180. * M_PI) * sin(lon / 180. * M_PI);
1592  x[2] = radius * sin(lat / 180. * M_PI);
1593 }
1594 
1595 /*****************************************************************************/
1596 
1597 void get_met(
1598  ctl_t * ctl,
1599  double t,
1600  met_t ** met0,
1601  met_t ** met1) {
1602 
1603  static int init;
1604 
1605  met_t *mets;
1606 
1607  char filename[LEN];
1608 
1609  /* Set timer... */
1610  SELECT_TIMER("GET_MET", NVTX_READ);
1611 
1612  /* Init... */
1613  if (t == ctl->t_start || !init) {
1614  init = 1;
1615 
1616  get_met_help(t, -1, ctl->metbase, ctl->dt_met, filename);
1617  if (!read_met(ctl, filename, *met0))
1618  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
1619 
1620  get_met_help(t + 1.0 * ctl->direction, 1, ctl->metbase, ctl->dt_met,
1621  filename);
1622  if (!read_met(ctl, filename, *met1))
1623  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
1624 #ifdef _OPENACC
1625  met_t *met0up = *met0;
1626  met_t *met1up = *met1;
1627 #pragma acc update device(met0up[:1],met1up[:1])
1628 #endif
1629  }
1630 
1631  /* Read new data for forward trajectories... */
1632  if (t > (*met1)->time && ctl->direction == 1) {
1633  mets = *met1;
1634  *met1 = *met0;
1635  *met0 = mets;
1636  get_met_help(t, 1, ctl->metbase, ctl->dt_met, filename);
1637  if (!read_met(ctl, filename, *met1))
1638  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
1639 #ifdef _OPENACC
1640  met_t *met1up = *met1;
1641 #pragma acc update device(met1up[:1])
1642 #endif
1643  }
1644 
1645  /* Read new data for backward trajectories... */
1646  if (t < (*met0)->time && ctl->direction == -1) {
1647  mets = *met1;
1648  *met1 = *met0;
1649  *met0 = mets;
1650  get_met_help(t, -1, ctl->metbase, ctl->dt_met, filename);
1651  if (!read_met(ctl, filename, *met0))
1652  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
1653 #ifdef _OPENACC
1654  met_t *met0up = *met0;
1655 #pragma acc update device(met0up[:1])
1656 #endif
1657  }
1658 
1659  /* Check that grids are consistent... */
1660  if ((*met0)->nx != (*met1)->nx
1661  || (*met0)->ny != (*met1)->ny || (*met0)->np != (*met1)->np)
1662  ERRMSG("Meteo grid dimensions do not match!");
1663  for (int ix = 0; ix < (*met0)->nx; ix++)
1664  if (fabs((*met0)->lon[ix] - (*met1)->lon[ix]) > 0.001)
1665  ERRMSG("Meteo grid longitudes do not match!");
1666  for (int iy = 0; iy < (*met0)->ny; iy++)
1667  if (fabs((*met0)->lat[iy] - (*met1)->lat[iy]) > 0.001)
1668  ERRMSG("Meteo grid latitudes do not match!");
1669  for (int ip = 0; ip < (*met0)->np; ip++)
1670  if (fabs((*met0)->p[ip] - (*met1)->p[ip]) > 0.001)
1671  ERRMSG("Meteo grid pressure levels do not match!");
1672 }
1673 
1674 /*****************************************************************************/
1675 
1676 void get_met_help(
1677  double t,
1678  int direct,
1679  char *metbase,
1680  double dt_met,
1681  char *filename) {
1682 
1683  char repl[LEN];
1684 
1685  double t6, r;
1686 
1687  int year, mon, day, hour, min, sec;
1688 
1689  /* Round time to fixed intervals... */
1690  if (direct == -1)
1691  t6 = floor(t / dt_met) * dt_met;
1692  else
1693  t6 = ceil(t / dt_met) * dt_met;
1694 
1695  /* Decode time... */
1696  jsec2time(t6, &year, &mon, &day, &hour, &min, &sec, &r);
1697 
1698  /* Set filename... */
1699  sprintf(filename, "%s_YYYY_MM_DD_HH.nc", metbase);
1700  sprintf(repl, "%d", year);
1701  get_met_replace(filename, "YYYY", repl);
1702  sprintf(repl, "%02d", mon);
1703  get_met_replace(filename, "MM", repl);
1704  sprintf(repl, "%02d", day);
1705  get_met_replace(filename, "DD", repl);
1706  sprintf(repl, "%02d", hour);
1707  get_met_replace(filename, "HH", repl);
1708 }
1709 
1710 /*****************************************************************************/
1711 
1712 void get_met_replace(
1713  char *orig,
1714  char *search,
1715  char *repl) {
1716 
1717  char buffer[LEN], *ch;
1718 
1719  /* Iterate... */
1720  for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
1721 
1722  /* Replace sub-string... */
1723  if (!(ch = strstr(orig, search)))
1724  return;
1725  strncpy(buffer, orig, (size_t) (ch - orig));
1726  buffer[ch - orig] = 0;
1727  sprintf(buffer + (ch - orig), "%s%s", repl, ch + strlen(search));
1728  orig[0] = 0;
1729  strcpy(orig, buffer);
1730  }
1731 }
1732 
1733 /*****************************************************************************/
1734 
1735 void intpol_met_space_3d(
1736  met_t * met,
1737  float array[EX][EY][EP],
1738  double p,
1739  double lon,
1740  double lat,
1741  double *var,
1742  int *ci,
1743  double *cw,
1744  int init) {
1745 
1746  /* Check longitude... */
1747  if (met->lon[met->nx - 1] > 180 && lon < 0)
1748  lon += 360;
1749 
1750  /* Get interpolation indices and weights... */
1751  if (init) {
1752  ci[0] = locate_irr(met->p, met->np, p);
1753  ci[1] = locate_reg(met->lon, met->nx, lon);
1754  ci[2] = locate_reg(met->lat, met->ny, lat);
1755  cw[0] = (met->p[ci[0] + 1] - p)
1756  / (met->p[ci[0] + 1] - met->p[ci[0]]);
1757  cw[1] = (met->lon[ci[1] + 1] - lon)
1758  / (met->lon[ci[1] + 1] - met->lon[ci[1]]);
1759  cw[2] = (met->lat[ci[2] + 1] - lat)
1760  / (met->lat[ci[2] + 1] - met->lat[ci[2]]);
1761  }
1762 
1763  /* Interpolate vertically... */
1764  double aux00 =
1765  cw[0] * (array[ci[1]][ci[2]][ci[0]] - array[ci[1]][ci[2]][ci[0] + 1])
1766  + array[ci[1]][ci[2]][ci[0] + 1];
1767  double aux01 =
1768  cw[0] * (array[ci[1]][ci[2] + 1][ci[0]] -
1769  array[ci[1]][ci[2] + 1][ci[0] + 1])
1770  + array[ci[1]][ci[2] + 1][ci[0] + 1];
1771  double aux10 =
1772  cw[0] * (array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2]][ci[0]] -
1773  array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2]][ci[0] + 1])
1774  + array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2]][ci[0] + 1];
1775  double aux11 =
1776  cw[0] * (array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2] + 1][ci[0]] -
1777  array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2] + 1][ci[0] + 1])
1778  + array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2] + 1][ci[0] + 1];
1779 
1780  /* Interpolate horizontally... */
1781  aux00 = cw[2] * (aux00 - aux01) + aux01;
1782  aux11 = cw[2] * (aux10 - aux11) + aux11;
1783  *var = cw[1] * (aux00 - aux11) + aux11;
1784 }
1785 
1786 
1787 /*****************************************************************************/
1788 
1789 void intpol_met_space_2d(
1790  met_t * met,
1791  float array[EX][EY],
1792  double lon,
1793  double lat,
1794  double *var,
1795  int *ci,
1796  double *cw,
1797  int init) {
1798 
1799  /* Check longitude... */
1800  if (met->lon[met->nx - 1] > 180 && lon < 0)
1801  lon += 360;
1802 
1803  /* Get interpolation indices and weights... */
1804  if (init) {
1805  ci[1] = locate_reg(met->lon, met->nx, lon);
1806  ci[2] = locate_reg(met->lat, met->ny, lat);
1807  cw[1] = (met->lon[ci[1] + 1] - lon)
1808  / (met->lon[ci[1] + 1] - met->lon[ci[1]]);
1809  cw[2] = (met->lat[ci[2] + 1] - lat)
1810  / (met->lat[ci[2] + 1] - met->lat[ci[2]]);
1811  }
1812 
1813  /* Set variables... */
1814  double aux00 = array[ci[1]][ci[2]];
1815  double aux01 = array[ci[1]][ci[2] + 1];
1816  double aux10 = array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2]];
1817  double aux11 = array[ci[1] + 1][ci[2] + 1];
1818 
1819  /* Interpolate horizontally... */
1820  if (isfinite(aux00) && isfinite(aux01))
1821  aux00 = cw[2] * (aux00 - aux01) + aux01;
1822  else if (cw[2] < 0.5)
1823  aux00 = aux01;
1824  if (isfinite(aux10) && isfinite(aux11))
1825  aux11 = cw[2] * (aux10 - aux11) + aux11;
1826  else if (cw[2] > 0.5)
1827  aux11 = aux10;
1828  if (isfinite(aux00) && isfinite(aux11))
1829  *var = cw[1] * (aux00 - aux11) + aux11;
1830  else {
1831  if (cw[1] > 0.5)
1832  *var = aux00;
1833  else
1834  *var = aux11;
1835  }
1836 }
1837 
1838 /*****************************************************************************/
1839 
1840 void intpol_met_time_3d(
1841  met_t * met0,
1842  float array0[EX][EY][EP],
1843  met_t * met1,
1844  float array1[EX][EY][EP],
1845  double ts,
1846  double p,
1847  double lon,
1848  double lat,
1849  double *var,
1850  int *ci,
1851  double *cw,
1852  int init) {
1853 
1854  double var0, var1, wt;
1855 
1856  /* Spatial interpolation... */
1857  intpol_met_space_3d(met0, array0, p, lon, lat, &var0, ci, cw, init);
1858  intpol_met_space_3d(met1, array1, p, lon, lat, &var1, ci, cw, init);
1859 
1860  /* Get weighting factor... */
1861  wt = (met1->time - ts) / (met1->time - met0->time);
1862 
1863  /* Interpolate... */
1864  *var = wt * (var0 - var1) + var1;
1865 }
1866 
1867 /*****************************************************************************/
1868 
1869 void intpol_met_time_2d(
1870  met_t * met0,
1871  float array0[EX][EY],
1872  met_t * met1,
1873  float array1[EX][EY],
1874  double ts,
1875  double lon,
1876  double lat,
1877  double *var,
1878  int *ci,
1879  double *cw,
1880  int init) {
1881 
1882  double var0, var1, wt;
1883 
1884  /* Spatial interpolation... */
1885  intpol_met_space_2d(met0, array0, lon, lat, &var0, ci, cw, init);
1886  intpol_met_space_2d(met1, array1, lon, lat, &var1, ci, cw, init);
1887 
1888  /* Get weighting factor... */
1889  wt = (met1->time - ts) / (met1->time - met0->time);
1890 
1891  /* Interpolate... */
1892  *var = wt * (var0 - var1) + var1;
1893 }
1894 
1895 /*****************************************************************************/
1896 
1897 void jsec2time(
1898  double jsec,
1899  int *year,
1900  int *mon,
1901  int *day,
1902  int *hour,
1903  int *min,
1904  int *sec,
1905  double *remain) {
1906 
1907  struct tm t0, *t1;
1908 
1909  t0.tm_year = 100;
1910  t0.tm_mon = 0;
1911  t0.tm_mday = 1;
1912  t0.tm_hour = 0;
1913  t0.tm_min = 0;
1914  t0.tm_sec = 0;
1915 
1916  time_t jsec0 = (time_t) jsec + timegm(&t0);
1917  t1 = gmtime(&jsec0);
1918 
1919  *year = t1->tm_year + 1900;
1920  *mon = t1->tm_mon + 1;
1921  *day = t1->tm_mday;
1922  *hour = t1->tm_hour;
1923  *min = t1->tm_min;
1924  *sec = t1->tm_sec;
1925  *remain = jsec - floor(jsec);
1926 }
1927 
1928 /*****************************************************************************/
1929 
1930 double lapse_rate(
1931  double t,
1932  double h2o) {
1933 
1934  /*
1935  Calculate moist adiabatic lapse rate [K/km] from temperature [K]
1936  and water vapor volume mixing ratio [1].
1937 
1938  Reference: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lapse_rate
1939  */
1940 
1941  const double a = RA * SQR(t), r = SH(h2o) / (1. - SH(h2o));
1942 
1943  return 1e3 * G0 * (a + LV * r * t) / (CPD * a + SQR(LV) * r * EPS);
1944 }
1945 
1946 /*****************************************************************************/
1947 
1948 int locate_irr(
1949  double *xx,
1950  int n,
1951  double x) {
1952 
1953  int ilo = 0;
1954  int ihi = n - 1;
1955  int i = (ihi + ilo) >> 1;
1956 
1957  if (xx[i] < xx[i + 1])
1958  while (ihi > ilo + 1) {
1959  i = (ihi + ilo) >> 1;
1960  if (xx[i] > x)
1961  ihi = i;
1962  else
1963  ilo = i;
1964  } else
1965  while (ihi > ilo + 1) {
1966  i = (ihi + ilo) >> 1;
1967  if (xx[i] <= x)
1968  ihi = i;
1969  else
1970  ilo = i;
1971  }
1972 
1973  return ilo;
1974 }
1975 
1976 /*****************************************************************************/
1977 
1978 int locate_reg(
1979  double *xx,
1980  int n,
1981  double x) {
1982 
1983  /* Calculate index... */
1984  int i = (int) ((x - xx[0]) / (xx[1] - xx[0]));
1985 
1986  /* Check range... */
1987  if (i < 0)
1988  i = 0;
1989  else if (i >= n - 2)
1990  i = n - 2;
1991 
1992  return i;
1993 }
1994 
1995 /*****************************************************************************/
1996 
1997 double nat_temperature(
1998  double p,
1999  double h2o,
2000  double hno3) {
2001 
2002  double p_hno3 = hno3 * p / 1.333224;
2003  double p_h2o = h2o * p / 1.333224;
2004  double a = 0.009179 - 0.00088 * log10(p_h2o);
2005  double b = (38.9855 - log10(p_hno3) - 2.7836 * log10(p_h2o)) / a;
2006  double c = -11397.0 / a;
2007  double tnat = (-b + sqrt(b * b - 4. * c)) / 2.;
2008  double x2 = (-b - sqrt(b * b - 4. * c)) / 2.;
2009  if (x2 > 0)
2010  tnat = x2;
2011 
2012  return tnat;
2013 }
2014 
2015 /*****************************************************************************/
2016 
2017 int read_atm(
2018  const char *filename,
2019  ctl_t * ctl,
2020  atm_t * atm) {
2021 
2022  FILE *in;
2023 
2024  char line[LEN], *tok;
2025 
2026  double t0;
2027 
2028  int dimid, ncid, varid;
2029 
2030  size_t nparts;
2031 
2032  /* Set timer... */
2033  SELECT_TIMER("READ_ATM", NVTX_READ);
2034 
2035  /* Init... */
2036  atm->np = 0;
2037 
2038  /* Write info... */
2039  printf("Read atmospheric data: %s\n", filename);
2040 
2041  /* Read ASCII data... */
2042  if (ctl->atm_type == 0) {
2043 
2044  /* Open file... */
2045  if (!(in = fopen(filename, "r"))) {
2046  WARN("File not found!");
2047  return 0;
2048  }
2049 
2050  /* Read line... */
2051  while (fgets(line, LEN, in)) {
2052 
2053  /* Read data... */
2054  TOK(line, tok, "%lg", atm->time[atm->np]);
2055  TOK(NULL, tok, "%lg", atm->p[atm->np]);
2056  TOK(NULL, tok, "%lg", atm->lon[atm->np]);
2057  TOK(NULL, tok, "%lg", atm->lat[atm->np]);
2058  for (int iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
2059  TOK(NULL, tok, "%lg", atm->q[iq][atm->np]);
2060 
2061  /* Convert altitude to pressure... */
2062  atm->p[atm->np] = P(atm->p[atm->np]);
2063 
2064  /* Increment data point counter... */
2065  if ((++atm->np) > NP)
2066  ERRMSG("Too many data points!");
2067  }
2068 
2069  /* Close file... */
2070  fclose(in);
2071  }
2072 
2073  /* Read binary data... */
2074  else if (ctl->atm_type == 1) {
2075 
2076  /* Open file... */
2077  if (!(in = fopen(filename, "r")))
2078  return 0;
2079 
2080  /* Read data... */
2081  FREAD(&atm->np, int,
2082  1,
2083  in);
2084  FREAD(atm->time, double,
2085  (size_t) atm->np,
2086  in);
2087  FREAD(atm->p, double,
2088  (size_t) atm->np,
2089  in);
2090  FREAD(atm->lon, double,
2091  (size_t) atm->np,
2092  in);
2093  FREAD(atm->lat, double,
2094  (size_t) atm->np,
2095  in);
2096  for (int iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
2097  FREAD(atm->q[iq], double,
2098  (size_t) atm->np,
2099  in);
2100 
2101  /* Close file... */
2102  fclose(in);
2103  }
2104 
2105  /* Read netCDF data... */
2106  else if (ctl->atm_type == 2) {
2107 
2108  /* Open file... */
2109  if (nc_open(filename, NC_NOWRITE, &ncid) != NC_NOERR)
2110  return 0;
2111 
2112  /* Get dimensions... */
2113  NC(nc_inq_dimid(ncid, "NPARTS", &dimid));
2114  NC(nc_inq_dimlen(ncid, dimid, &nparts));
2115  atm->np = (int) nparts;
2116  if (atm->np > NP)
2117  ERRMSG("Too many particles!");
2118 
2119  /* Get time... */
2120  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "time", &varid));
2121  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, &t0));
2122  for (int ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++)
2123  atm->time[ip] = t0;
2124 
2125  /* Read geolocations... */
2126  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "PRESS", &varid));
2127  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->p));
2128  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "LON", &varid));
2129  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->lon));
2130  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "LAT", &varid));
2131  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->lat));
2132 
2133  /* Read variables... */
2134  if (ctl->qnt_p >= 0)
2135  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "PRESS", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2136  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_p]));
2137  if (ctl->qnt_t >= 0)
2138  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "TEMP", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2139  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_t]));
2140  if (ctl->qnt_u >= 0)
2141  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "U", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2142  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_u]));
2143  if (ctl->qnt_v >= 0)
2144  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "V", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2145  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_v]));
2146  if (ctl->qnt_w >= 0)
2147  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "W", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2148  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_w]));
2149  if (ctl->qnt_h2o >= 0)
2150  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "SH", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2151  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_h2o]));
2152  if (ctl->qnt_o3 >= 0)
2153  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "O3", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2154  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_o3]));
2155  if (ctl->qnt_theta >= 0)
2156  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "THETA", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2157  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_theta]));
2158  if (ctl->qnt_pv >= 0)
2159  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, "PV", &varid) == NC_NOERR)
2160  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, atm->q[ctl->qnt_pv]));
2161 
2162  /* Check data... */
2163  for (int ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++)
2164  if (fabs(atm->lon[ip]) > 360 || fabs(atm->lat[ip]) > 90
2165  || (ctl->qnt_t >= 0 && fabs(atm->q[ctl->qnt_t][ip]) > 350)
2166  || (ctl->qnt_h2o >= 0 && fabs(atm->q[ctl->qnt_h2o][ip]) > 1)
2167  || (ctl->qnt_theta >= 0 && fabs(atm->q[ctl->qnt_theta][ip]) > 1e10)
2168  || (ctl->qnt_pv >= 0 && fabs(atm->q[ctl->qnt_pv][ip]) > 1e10)) {
2169  atm->time[ip] = GSL_NAN;
2170  atm->p[ip] = GSL_NAN;
2171  atm->lon[ip] = GSL_NAN;
2172  atm->lat[ip] = GSL_NAN;
2173  for (int iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
2174  atm->q[iq][ip] = GSL_NAN;
2175  } else {
2176  if (ctl->qnt_h2o >= 0)
2177  atm->q[ctl->qnt_h2o][ip] *= 1.608;
2178  if (ctl->qnt_pv >= 0)
2179  atm->q[ctl->qnt_pv][ip] *= 1e6;
2180  if (atm->lon[ip] > 180)
2181  atm->lon[ip] -= 360;
2182  }
2183 
2184  /* Close file... */
2185  NC(nc_close(ncid));
2186  }
2187 
2188  /* Error... */
2189  else
2190  ERRMSG("Atmospheric data type not supported!");
2191 
2192  /* Check number of points... */
2193  if (atm->np < 1)
2194  ERRMSG("Can not read any data!");
2195 
2196  /* Return success... */
2197  return 1;
2198 }

2200 /*****************************************************************************/
2201 
2202 void read_ctl(
2203  const char *filename,
2204  int argc,
2205  char *argv[],
2206  ctl_t * ctl) {
2207 
2208  /* Set timer... */
2209  SELECT_TIMER("READ_CTL", NVTX_READ);
2210 
2211  /* Write info... */
2212  printf("\nMassive-Parallel Trajectory Calculations (MPTRAC)\n"
2213  "(executable: %s | compiled: %s, %s)\n\n",
2214  argv[0], __DATE__, __TIME__);
2215 
2216  /* Initialize quantity indices... */
2217  ctl->qnt_ens = -1;
2218  ctl->qnt_m = -1;
2219  ctl->qnt_vmr = -1;
2220  ctl->qnt_r = -1;
2221  ctl->qnt_rho = -1;
2222  ctl->qnt_ps = -1;
2223  ctl->qnt_ts = -1;
2224  ctl->qnt_zs = -1;
2225  ctl->qnt_us = -1;
2226  ctl->qnt_vs = -1;
2227  ctl->qnt_pbl = -1;
2228  ctl->qnt_pt = -1;

2605  ctl->grid_nx =
2606  (int) scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "GRID_NX", -1, "360", NULL);
2607  ctl->grid_lat0 =
2608  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "GRID_LAT0", -1, "-90", NULL);
2609  ctl->grid_lat1 =
2610  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "GRID_LAT1", -1, "90", NULL);
2611  ctl->grid_ny =
2612  (int) scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "GRID_NY", -1, "180", NULL);
2613 
2614  /* Output of profile data... */
2615  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_BASENAME", -1, "-",
2616  ctl->prof_basename);
2617  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_OBSFILE", -1, "-", ctl->prof_obsfile);
2618  ctl->prof_z0 = scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_Z0", -1, "0", NULL);
2619  ctl->prof_z1 = scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_Z1", -1, "60", NULL);
2620  ctl->prof_nz =
2621  (int) scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_NZ", -1, "60", NULL);
2622  ctl->prof_lon0 =
2623  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_LON0", -1, "-180", NULL);
2624  ctl->prof_lon1 =
2625  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_LON1", -1, "180", NULL);
2626  ctl->prof_nx =
2627  (int) scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_NX", -1, "360", NULL);
2628  ctl->prof_lat0 =
2629  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_LAT0", -1, "-90", NULL);
2630  ctl->prof_lat1 =
2631  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_LAT1", -1, "90", NULL);
2632  ctl->prof_ny =
2633  (int) scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "PROF_NY", -1, "180", NULL);
2634 
2635  /* Output of sample data... */
2636  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "SAMPLE_BASENAME", -1, "-",
2637  ctl->sample_basename);
2638  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "SAMPLE_OBSFILE", -1, "-",
2639  ctl->sample_obsfile);
2640  ctl->sample_dx =
2641  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "SAMPLE_DX", -1, "50", NULL);
2642  ctl->sample_dz =
2643  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "SAMPLE_DZ", -1, "-999", NULL);
2644 
2645  /* Output of station data... */
2646  scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "STAT_BASENAME", -1, "-",
2647  ctl->stat_basename);
2648  ctl->stat_lon = scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "STAT_LON", -1, "0", NULL);
2649  ctl->stat_lat = scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "STAT_LAT", -1, "0", NULL);
2650  ctl->stat_r = scan_ctl(filename, argc, argv, "STAT_R", -1, "50", NULL);
2651 }
2652 
2653 /*****************************************************************************/
2654 
2655 int read_met(
2656  ctl_t * ctl,
2657  char *filename,
2658  met_t * met) {
2659 
2660  int ncid;
2661 
2662  /* Write info... */
2663  printf("Read meteorological data: %s\n", filename);
2664 
2665  /* Open netCDF file... */
2666  if (nc__open(filename, ctl->read_mode, &ctl->chunkszhint, &ncid) !=
2667  NC_NOERR) {
2668  WARN("File not found!");
2669  return 0;
2670  }
2671 
2672  /* Read coordinates of meteorological data... */
2673  read_met_grid(filename, ncid, ctl, met);
2674 
2675  /* Read meteo data on vertical levels... */
2676  read_met_levels(ncid, ctl, met);
2677 
2678  /* Extrapolate data for lower boundary... */
2679  read_met_extrapolate(met);
2680 
2681  /* Read surface data... */
2682  read_met_surface(ncid, met);
2683 
2684  /* Create periodic boundary conditions... */
2685  read_met_periodic(met);
2686 
2687  /* Downsampling... */
2688  read_met_sample(ctl, met);
2689 
2690  /* Calculate geopotential heights... */
2691  read_met_geopot(ctl, met);
2692 
2693  /* Calculate potential vorticity... */
2694  read_met_pv(met);
2695 
2696  /* Calculate boundary layer data... */
2697  read_met_pbl(met);
2698 
2699  /* Calculate tropopause data... */
2700  read_met_tropo(ctl, met);
2701 
2702  /* Calculate cloud properties... */
2703  read_met_cloud(met);
2704 
2705  /* Calculate convective available potential energy... */
2706  read_met_cape(met);
2707 
2708  /* Detrending... */
2709  read_met_detrend(ctl, met);
2710 
2711  /* Close file... */
2712  NC(nc_close(ncid));
2713 
2714  /* Return success... */
2715  return 1;
2716 }
2717 
2718 /*****************************************************************************/
2719 
2720 void read_met_cape(
2721  met_t * met) {
2722 
2723  /* Set timer... */
2724  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_CAPE", NVTX_READ);
2725 
2726  /* Vertical spacing (about 100 m)... */
2727  const double pfac = 1.01439, dz0 = RI / MA / G0 * log(pfac);
2728 
2729  /* Loop over columns... */
2730 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2731  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
2732  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
2733 
2734  /* Get potential temperature and water vapor vmr at lowest 50 hPa... */
2735  int n = 0;
2736  double h2o = 0, t, theta = 0;
2737  double pbot = GSL_MIN(met->ps[ix][iy], met->p[0]);
2738  double ptop = pbot - 50.;
2739  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
2740  if (met->p[ip] <= pbot) {
2741  theta += THETA(met->p[ip], met->t[ix][iy][ip]);
2742  h2o += met->h2o[ix][iy][ip];
2743  n++;
2744  }
2745  if (met->p[ip] < ptop && n > 0)
2746  break;
2747  }
2748  theta /= n;
2749  h2o /= n;
2750 
2751  /* Cannot compute anything if water vapor is missing... */
2752  met->plcl[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
2753  met->plfc[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
2754  met->pel[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
2755  met->cape[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
2756  if (h2o <= 0)
2757  continue;
2758 
2759  /* Find lifted condensation level (LCL)... */
2760  ptop = P(20.);
2761  pbot = met->ps[ix][iy];
2762  do {
2763  met->plcl[ix][iy] = (float) (0.5 * (pbot + ptop));
2764  t = theta / pow(1000. / met->plcl[ix][iy], 0.286);
2765  if (RH(met->plcl[ix][iy], t, h2o) > 100.)
2766  ptop = met->plcl[ix][iy];
2767  else
2768  pbot = met->plcl[ix][iy];
2769  } while (pbot - ptop > 0.1);
2770 
2771  /* Calculate level of free convection (LFC), equilibrium level (EL),
2772  and convective available potential energy (CAPE)... */
2773  double dcape = 0, dcape_old, dz, h2o_env, p = met->plcl[ix][iy],
2774  psat, t_env;
2775  ptop = 0.75 * clim_tropo(met->time, met->lat[iy]);
2776  met->cape[ix][iy] = 0;
2777  do {
2778  dz = dz0 * TVIRT(t, h2o);
2779  p /= pfac;
2780  t -= lapse_rate(t, h2o) * dz;
2781  psat = PSAT(t);
2782  h2o = psat / (p - (1. - EPS) * psat);
2783  INTPOL_INIT;
2784  intpol_met_space_3d(met, met->t, p, met->lon[ix], met->lat[iy],
2785  &t_env, ci, cw, 1);
2786  intpol_met_space_3d(met, met->h2o, p, met->lon[ix], met->lat[iy],
2787  &h2o_env, ci, cw, 0);
2788  dcape_old = dcape;
2789  dcape = 1e3 * G0 * (TVIRT(t, h2o) - TVIRT(t_env, h2o_env)) /
2790  TVIRT(t_env, h2o_env) * dz;
2791  if (dcape > 0) {
2792  met->cape[ix][iy] += (float) dcape;
2793  if (!isfinite(met->plfc[ix][iy]))
2794  met->plfc[ix][iy] = (float) p;
2795  } else if (dcape_old > 0)
2796  met->pel[ix][iy] = (float) p;
2797  } while (p > ptop);
2798  }
2799 }
2800 
2801 /*****************************************************************************/
2802 
2803 void read_met_cloud(
2804  met_t * met) {
2805 
2806  /* Set timer... */
2807  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_CLOUD", NVTX_READ);
2808 
2809  /* Loop over columns... */
2810 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2811  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
2812  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
2813 
2814  /* Init... */
2815  met->pc[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
2816  met->cl[ix][iy] = 0;
2817 
2818  /* Loop over pressure levels... */
2819  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np - 1; ip++) {
2820 
2821  /* Check pressure... */
2822  if (met->p[ip] > met->ps[ix][iy] || met->p[ip] < P(20.))
2823  continue;
2824 
2825  /* Get cloud top pressure ... */
2826  if (met->iwc[ix][iy][ip] > 0 || met->lwc[ix][iy][ip] > 0)
2827  met->pc[ix][iy] = (float) met->p[ip + 1];
2828 
2829  /* Get cloud water... */
2830  met->cl[ix][iy] += (float)
2831  (0.5 * (met->iwc[ix][iy][ip] + met->iwc[ix][iy][ip + 1]
2832  + met->lwc[ix][iy][ip] + met->lwc[ix][iy][ip + 1])
2833  * 100. * (met->p[ip] - met->p[ip + 1]) / G0);
2834  }
2835  }
2836 }
2837 
2838 /*****************************************************************************/
2839 
2840 void read_met_detrend(
2841  ctl_t * ctl,
2842  met_t * met) {
2843 
2844  met_t *help;
2845 
2846  /* Check parameters... */
2847  if (ctl->met_detrend <= 0)
2848  return;
2849 
2850  /* Set timer... */
2851  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_DETREND", NVTX_READ);
2852 
2853  /* Allocate... */
2854  ALLOC(help, met_t, 1);
2855 
2856  /* Calculate standard deviation... */
2857  double sigma = ctl->met_detrend / 2.355;
2858  double tssq = 2. * SQR(sigma);
2859 
2860  /* Calculate box size in latitude... */
2861  int sy = (int) (3. * DY2DEG(sigma) / fabs(met->lat[1] - met->lat[0]));
2862  sy = GSL_MIN(GSL_MAX(1, sy), met->ny / 2);
2863 
2864  /* Calculate background... */
2865 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2866  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++) {
2867  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
2868 
2869  /* Calculate Cartesian coordinates... */
2870  double x0[3];
2871  geo2cart(0.0, met->lon[ix], met->lat[iy], x0);
2872 
2873  /* Calculate box size in longitude... */
2874  int sx =
2875  (int) (3. * DX2DEG(sigma, met->lat[iy]) /
2876  fabs(met->lon[1] - met->lon[0]));
2877  sx = GSL_MIN(GSL_MAX(1, sx), met->nx / 2);
2878 
2879  /* Init... */
2880  float wsum = 0;
2881  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
2882  help->t[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
2883  help->u[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
2884  help->v[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
2885  help->w[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
2886  }
2887 
2888  /* Loop over neighboring grid points... */
2889  for (int ix2 = ix - sx; ix2 <= ix + sx; ix2++) {
2890  int ix3 = ix2;
2891  if (ix3 < 0)
2892  ix3 += met->nx;
2893  else if (ix3 >= met->nx)
2894  ix3 -= met->nx;
2895  for (int iy2 = GSL_MAX(iy - sy, 0);
2896  iy2 <= GSL_MIN(iy + sy, met->ny - 1); iy2++) {
2897 
2898  /* Calculate Cartesian coordinates... */
2899  double x1[3];
2900  geo2cart(0.0, met->lon[ix3], met->lat[iy2], x1);
2901 
2902  /* Calculate weighting factor... */
2903  float w = (float) exp(-DIST2(x0, x1) / tssq);
2904 
2905  /* Add data... */
2906  wsum += w;
2907  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
2908  help->t[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->t[ix3][iy2][ip];
2909  help->u[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->u[ix3][iy2][ip];
2910  help->v[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->v[ix3][iy2][ip];
2911  help->w[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->w[ix3][iy2][ip];
2912  }
2913  }
2914  }
2915 
2916  /* Normalize... */
2917  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
2918  help->t[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
2919  help->u[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
2920  help->v[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
2921  help->w[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
2922  }
2923  }
2924  }
2925 
2926  /* Subtract background... */
2927 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2928  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
2929  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
2930  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
2931  met->t[ix][iy][ip] -= help->t[ix][iy][ip];
2932  met->u[ix][iy][ip] -= help->u[ix][iy][ip];
2933  met->v[ix][iy][ip] -= help->v[ix][iy][ip];
2934  met->w[ix][iy][ip] -= help->w[ix][iy][ip];
2935  }
2936 
2937  /* Free... */
2938  free(help);
2939 }
2940 
2941 /*****************************************************************************/
2942 
2943 void read_met_extrapolate(
2944  met_t * met) {
2945 
2946  /* Set timer... */
2947  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_EXTRAPOLATE", NVTX_READ);
2948 
2949  /* Loop over columns... */
2950 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2951  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
2952  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
2953 
2954  /* Find lowest valid data point... */
2955  int ip0;
2956  for (ip0 = met->np - 1; ip0 >= 0; ip0--)
2957  if (!isfinite(met->t[ix][iy][ip0])
2958  || !isfinite(met->u[ix][iy][ip0])
2959  || !isfinite(met->v[ix][iy][ip0])
2960  || !isfinite(met->w[ix][iy][ip0]))
2961  break;
2962 
2963  /* Extrapolate... */
2964  for (int ip = ip0; ip >= 0; ip--) {
2965  met->t[ix][iy][ip] = met->t[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2966  met->u[ix][iy][ip] = met->u[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2967  met->v[ix][iy][ip] = met->v[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2968  met->w[ix][iy][ip] = met->w[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2969  met->h2o[ix][iy][ip] = met->h2o[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2970  met->o3[ix][iy][ip] = met->o3[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2971  met->lwc[ix][iy][ip] = met->lwc[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2972  met->iwc[ix][iy][ip] = met->iwc[ix][iy][ip + 1];
2973  }
2974  }
2975 }
2976 
2977 /*****************************************************************************/
2978 
2979 void read_met_geopot(
2980  ctl_t * ctl,
2981  met_t * met) {
2982 
2983  static float help[EP][EX][EY];
2984 
2985  double logp[EP];
2986 
2987  int dx = ctl->met_geopot_sx, dy = ctl->met_geopot_sy;
2988 
2989  /* Set timer... */
2990  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_GEOPOT", NVTX_READ);
2991 
2992  /* Calculate log pressure... */
2993 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2994  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
2995  logp[ip] = log(met->p[ip]);
2996 
2997  /* Apply hydrostatic equation to calculate geopotential heights... */
2998 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
2999  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3000  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3001 
3002  /* Get surface height and pressure... */
3003  double zs = met->zs[ix][iy];
3004  double lnps = log(met->ps[ix][iy]);
3005 
3006  /* Get temperature and water vapor vmr at the surface... */
3007  int ip0 = locate_irr(met->p, met->np, met->ps[ix][iy]);
3008  double ts = LIN(met->p[ip0], met->t[ix][iy][ip0], met->p[ip0 + 1],
3009  met->t[ix][iy][ip0 + 1], met->ps[ix][iy]);
3010  double h2os = LIN(met->p[ip0], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip0], met->p[ip0 + 1],
3011  met->h2o[ix][iy][ip0 + 1], met->ps[ix][iy]);
3012 
3013  /* Upper part of profile... */
3014  met->z[ix][iy][ip0 + 1]
3015  = (float) (zs +
3016  ZDIFF(lnps, ts, h2os, logp[ip0 + 1],
3017  met->t[ix][iy][ip0 + 1], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip0 + 1]));
3018  for (int ip = ip0 + 2; ip < met->np; ip++)
3019  met->z[ix][iy][ip]
3020  = (float) (met->z[ix][iy][ip - 1] +
3021  ZDIFF(logp[ip - 1], met->t[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3022  met->h2o[ix][iy][ip - 1], logp[ip],
3023  met->t[ix][iy][ip], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip]));
3024 
3025  /* Lower part of profile... */
3026  met->z[ix][iy][ip0]
3027  = (float) (zs +
3028  ZDIFF(lnps, ts, h2os, logp[ip0],
3029  met->t[ix][iy][ip0], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip0]));
3030  for (int ip = ip0 - 1; ip >= 0; ip--)
3031  met->z[ix][iy][ip]
3032  = (float) (met->z[ix][iy][ip + 1] +
3033  ZDIFF(logp[ip + 1], met->t[ix][iy][ip + 1],
3034  met->h2o[ix][iy][ip + 1], logp[ip],
3035  met->t[ix][iy][ip], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip]));
3036  }
3037 
3038  /* Check control parameters... */
3039  if (dx == 0 || dy == 0)
3040  return;
3041 
3042  /* Default smoothing parameters... */
3043  if (dx < 0 || dy < 0) {
3044  if (fabs(met->lon[1] - met->lon[0]) < 0.5) {
3045  dx = 3;
3046  dy = 2;
3047  } else {
3048  dx = 6;
3049  dy = 4;
3050  }
3051  }
3052 
3053  /* Calculate weights for smoothing... */
3054  float ws[dx + 1][dy + 1];
3055 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3056  for (int ix = 0; ix <= dx; ix++)
3057  for (int iy = 0; iy < dy; iy++)
3058  ws[ix][iy] = (1.0f - (float) ix / (float) dx)
3059  * (1.0f - (float) iy / (float) dy);
3060 
3061  /* Copy data... */
3062 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) collapse(3)
3063  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3064  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3065  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3066  help[ip][ix][iy] = met->z[ix][iy][ip];
3067 
3068  /* Horizontal smoothing... */
3069 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) collapse(3)
3070  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3071  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3072  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3073  float res = 0, wsum = 0;
3074  int iy0 = GSL_MAX(iy - dy + 1, 0);
3075  int iy1 = GSL_MIN(iy + dy - 1, met->ny - 1);
3076  for (int ix2 = ix - dx + 1; ix2 <= ix + dx - 1; ++ix2) {
3077  int ix3 = ix2;
3078  if (ix3 < 0)
3079  ix3 += met->nx;
3080  else if (ix3 >= met->nx)
3081  ix3 -= met->nx;
3082  for (int iy2 = iy0; iy2 <= iy1; ++iy2)
3083  if (isfinite(help[ip][ix3][iy2])) {
3084  float w = ws[abs(ix - ix2)][abs(iy - iy2)];
3085  res += w * help[ip][ix3][iy2];
3086  wsum += w;
3087  }
3088  }
3089  if (wsum > 0)
3090  met->z[ix][iy][ip] = res / wsum;
3091  else
3092  met->z[ix][iy][ip] = GSL_NAN;
3093  }
3094 }
3095 
3096 /*****************************************************************************/
3097 
3098 void read_met_grid(
3099  char *filename,
3100  int ncid,
3101  ctl_t * ctl,
3102  met_t * met) {
3103 
3104  char levname[LEN], tstr[10];
3105 
3106  int dimid, varid;
3107 
3108  size_t np, nx, ny;
3109 
3110  /* Set timer... */
3111  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_GRID", NVTX_READ);
3112 
3113  /* Get time from filename... */
3114  sprintf(tstr, "%.4s", &filename[strlen(filename) - 16]);
3115  int year = atoi(tstr);
3116  sprintf(tstr, "%.2s", &filename[strlen(filename) - 11]);
3117  int mon = atoi(tstr);
3118  sprintf(tstr, "%.2s", &filename[strlen(filename) - 8]);
3119  int day = atoi(tstr);
3120  sprintf(tstr, "%.2s", &filename[strlen(filename) - 5]);
3121  int hour = atoi(tstr);
3122  time2jsec(year, mon, day, hour, 0, 0, 0, &met->time);
3123 
3124  /* Get grid dimensions... */
3125  NC(nc_inq_dimid(ncid, "lon", &dimid));
3126  NC(nc_inq_dimlen(ncid, dimid, &nx));
3127  if (nx < 2 || nx > EX)
3128  ERRMSG("Number of longitudes out of range!");
3129 
3130  NC(nc_inq_dimid(ncid, "lat", &dimid));
3131  NC(nc_inq_dimlen(ncid, dimid, &ny));
3132  if (ny < 2 || ny > EY)
3133  ERRMSG("Number of latitudes out of range!");
3134 
3135  sprintf(levname, "lev");
3136  NC(nc_inq_dimid(ncid, levname, &dimid));
3137  NC(nc_inq_dimlen(ncid, dimid, &np));
3138  if (np == 1) {
3139  sprintf(levname, "lev_2");
3140  if (nc_inq_dimid(ncid, levname, &dimid) != NC_NOERR) {
3141  sprintf(levname, "plev");
3142  nc_inq_dimid(ncid, levname, &dimid);
3143  }
3144  NC(nc_inq_dimlen(ncid, dimid, &np));
3145  }
3146  if (np < 2 || np > EP)
3147  ERRMSG("Number of levels out of range!");
3148 
3149  /* Store dimensions... */
3150  met->np = (int) np;
3151  met->nx = (int) nx;
3152  met->ny = (int) ny;
3153 
3154  /* Read longitudes and latitudes... */
3155  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "lon", &varid));
3156  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, met->lon));
3157  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, "lat", &varid));
3158  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, met->lat));
3159 
3160  /* Read pressure levels... */
3161  if (ctl->met_np <= 0) {
3162  NC(nc_inq_varid(ncid, levname, &varid));
3163  NC(nc_get_var_double(ncid, varid, met->p));
3164  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3165  met->p[ip] /= 100.;
3166  }
3167 
3168  /* Set pressure levels... */
3169  else {
3170  met->np = ctl->met_np;
3171  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3172  met->p[ip] = ctl->met_p[ip];
3173  }
3174 
3175  /* Check ordering of pressure levels... */
3176  for (int ip = 1; ip < met->np; ip++)
3177  if (met->p[ip - 1] < met->p[ip])
3178  ERRMSG("Pressure levels must be descending!");
3179 }

3189  float scl,

3193

3198  if (nc_inq_varid(ncid, varname2, &varid) != NC_NOERR)

3200

3207

3210  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3211  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3212  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {

3217  else
3218  dest[ix][iy][ip] = GSL_NAN;
3219  }

3274 /*****************************************************************************/
3275 
3276 void read_met_levels(
3277  int ncid,
3278  ctl_t * ctl,
3279  met_t * met) {
3280 
3281  /* Set timer... */
3282  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_LEVELS", NVTX_READ);
3283 
3284  /* Read meteorological data... */
3285  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "t", "T", met, met->t, 1.0, 1))
3286  ERRMSG("Cannot read temperature!");
3287  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "u", "U", met, met->u, 1.0, 1))
3288  ERRMSG("Cannot read zonal wind!");
3289  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "v", "V", met, met->v, 1.0, 1))
3290  ERRMSG("Cannot read meridional wind!");
3291  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "w", "W", met, met->w, 0.01f, 1))
3292  WARN("Cannot read vertical velocity");
3293  if (!read_met_help_3d
3294  (ncid, "q", "Q", met, met->h2o, (float) (MA / MH2O), 1))
3295  WARN("Cannot read specific humidity!");
3296  if (!read_met_help_3d
3297  (ncid, "o3", "O3", met, met->o3, (float) (MA / MO3), 1))
3298  WARN("Cannot read ozone data!");
3299  if (ctl->met_cloud == 1 || ctl->met_cloud == 3) {
3300  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "clwc", "CLWC", met, met->lwc, 1.0, 1))
3301  WARN("Cannot read cloud liquid water content!");
3302  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "ciwc", "CIWC", met, met->iwc, 1.0, 1))
3303  WARN("Cannot read cloud ice water content!");
3304  }
3305  if (ctl->met_cloud == 2 || ctl->met_cloud == 3) {
3306  if (!read_met_help_3d
3307  (ncid, "crwc", "CRWC", met, met->lwc, 1.0, ctl->met_cloud == 2))
3308  WARN("Cannot read cloud rain water content!");
3309  if (!read_met_help_3d
3310  (ncid, "cswc", "CSWC", met, met->iwc, 1.0, ctl->met_cloud == 2))
3311  WARN("Cannot read cloud snow water content!");
3312  }
3313 
3314  /* Transfer from model levels to pressure levels... */
3315  if (ctl->met_np > 0) {
3316 
3317  /* Read pressure on model levels... */
3318  if (!read_met_help_3d(ncid, "pl", "PL", met, met->pl, 0.01f, 1))
3319  ERRMSG("Cannot read pressure on model levels!");
3320 
3321  /* Vertical interpolation from model to pressure levels... */
3322  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->t);
3323  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->u);
3324  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->v);
3325  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->w);
3326  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->h2o);
3327  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->o3);
3328  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->lwc);
3329  read_met_ml2pl(ctl, met, met->iwc);
3330  }
3331 }
3332 
3333 /*****************************************************************************/
3334 
3335 void read_met_ml2pl(
3336  ctl_t * ctl,
3337  met_t * met,
3338  float var[EX][EY][EP]) {
3339 
3340  double aux[EP], p[EP];
3341 
3342  /* Set timer... */
3343  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_ML2PL", NVTX_READ);
3344 
3345  /* Loop over columns... */
3346 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(aux,p)
3347  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3348  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3349 
3350  /* Copy pressure profile... */
3351  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3352  p[ip] = met->pl[ix][iy][ip];
3353 
3354  /* Interpolate... */
3355  for (int ip = 0; ip < ctl->met_np; ip++) {
3356  double pt = ctl->met_p[ip];
3357  if ((pt > p[0] && p[0] > p[1]) || (pt < p[0] && p[0] < p[1]))
3358  pt = p[0];
3359  else if ((pt > p[met->np - 1] && p[1] > p[0])
3360  || (pt < p[met->np - 1] && p[1] < p[0]))
3361  pt = p[met->np - 1];
3362  int ip2 = locate_irr(p, met->np, pt);
3363  aux[ip] = LIN(p[ip2], var[ix][iy][ip2],
3364  p[ip2 + 1], var[ix][iy][ip2 + 1], pt);
3365  }
3366 
3367  /* Copy data... */
3368  for (int ip = 0; ip < ctl->met_np; ip++)
3369  var[ix][iy][ip] = (float) aux[ip];
3370  }
3371 }
3372 
3373 /*****************************************************************************/
3374 
3375 void read_met_pbl(
3376  met_t * met) {
3377 
3378  /* Set timer... */
3379  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_PBL", NVTX_READ);
3380 
3381  /* Parameters used to estimate the height of the PBL
3382  (e.g., Vogelezang and Holtslag, 1996; Seidel et al., 2012)... */
3383  const double rib_crit = 0.25, dz = 0.05, umin = 5.0;
3384 
3385  /* Loop over grid points... */
3386 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3387  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3388  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3389 
3390  /* Set bottom level of PBL... */
3391  double pbl_bot = met->ps[ix][iy] + DZ2DP(dz, met->ps[ix][iy]);
3392 
3393  /* Find lowest level near the bottom... */
3394  int ip;
3395  for (ip = 1; ip < met->np; ip++)
3396  if (met->p[ip] < pbl_bot)
3397  break;
3398 
3399  /* Get near surface data... */
3400  double zs = LIN(met->p[ip - 1], met->z[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3401  met->p[ip], met->z[ix][iy][ip], pbl_bot);
3402  double ts = LIN(met->p[ip - 1], met->t[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3403  met->p[ip], met->t[ix][iy][ip], pbl_bot);
3404  double us = LIN(met->p[ip - 1], met->u[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3405  met->p[ip], met->u[ix][iy][ip], pbl_bot);
3406  double vs = LIN(met->p[ip - 1], met->v[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3407  met->p[ip], met->v[ix][iy][ip], pbl_bot);
3408  double h2os = LIN(met->p[ip - 1], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip - 1],
3409  met->p[ip], met->h2o[ix][iy][ip], pbl_bot);
3410  double tvs = THETAVIRT(pbl_bot, ts, h2os);
3411 
3412  /* Init... */
3413  double rib, rib_old = 0, vh2;
3414 
3415  /* Loop over levels... */
3416  for (; ip < met->np; ip++) {
3417 
3418  /* Get squared horizontal wind speed... */
3419  vh2 = SQR(met->u[ix][iy][ip] - us) + SQR(met->v[ix][iy][ip] - vs);
3420  vh2 = GSL_MAX(vh2, SQR(umin));
3421 
3422  /* Calculate bulk Richardson number... */
3423  rib = G0 * 1e3 * (met->z[ix][iy][ip] - zs) / tvs
3424  * (THETAVIRT(met->p[ip], met->t[ix][iy][ip],
3425  met->h2o[ix][iy][ip]) - tvs) / vh2;
3426 
3427  /* Check for critical value... */
3428  if (rib >= rib_crit) {
3429  met->pbl[ix][iy] = (float) (LIN(rib_old, met->p[ip - 1],
3430  rib, met->p[ip], rib_crit));
3431  if (met->pbl[ix][iy] > pbl_bot)
3432  met->pbl[ix][iy] = (float) pbl_bot;
3433  break;
3434  }
3435 
3436  /* Save Richardson number... */
3437  rib_old = rib;
3438  }
3439  }
3440 }
3441 
3442 /*****************************************************************************/
3443 
3444 void read_met_periodic(
3445  met_t * met) {
3446 
3447  /* Set timer... */
3448  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_PERIODIC", NVTX_READ);
3449 
3450  /* Check longitudes... */
3451  if (!(fabs(met->lon[met->nx - 1] - met->lon[0]
3452  + met->lon[1] - met->lon[0] - 360) < 0.01))
3453  return;
3454 
3455  /* Increase longitude counter... */
3456  if ((++met->nx) > EX)
3457  ERRMSG("Cannot create periodic boundary conditions!");
3458 
3459  /* Set longitude... */
3460  met->lon[met->nx - 1] = met->lon[met->nx - 2] + met->lon[1] - met->lon[0];
3461 
3462  /* Loop over latitudes and pressure levels... */
3463 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3464  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3465  met->ps[met->nx - 1][iy] = met->ps[0][iy];
3466  met->zs[met->nx - 1][iy] = met->zs[0][iy];
3467  met->ts[met->nx - 1][iy] = met->ts[0][iy];
3468  met->us[met->nx - 1][iy] = met->us[0][iy];
3469  met->vs[met->nx - 1][iy] = met->vs[0][iy];
3470  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
3471  met->t[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->t[0][iy][ip];
3472  met->u[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->u[0][iy][ip];
3473  met->v[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->v[0][iy][ip];
3474  met->w[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->w[0][iy][ip];
3475  met->h2o[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->h2o[0][iy][ip];
3476  met->o3[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->o3[0][iy][ip];
3477  met->lwc[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->lwc[0][iy][ip];
3478  met->iwc[met->nx - 1][iy][ip] = met->iwc[0][iy][ip];
3479  }
3480  }
3481 }
3482 
3483 /*****************************************************************************/
3484 
3485 void read_met_pv(
3486  met_t * met) {
3487 
3488  double pows[EP];
3489 
3490  /* Set timer... */
3491  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_PV", NVTX_READ);
3492 
3493  /* Set powers... */
3494 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3495  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++)
3496  pows[ip] = pow(1000. / met->p[ip], 0.286);
3497 
3498  /* Loop over grid points... */
3499 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3500  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++) {
3501 
3502  /* Set indices... */
3503  int ix0 = GSL_MAX(ix - 1, 0);
3504  int ix1 = GSL_MIN(ix + 1, met->nx - 1);
3505 
3506  /* Loop over grid points... */
3507  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3508 
3509  /* Set indices... */
3510  int iy0 = GSL_MAX(iy - 1, 0);
3511  int iy1 = GSL_MIN(iy + 1, met->ny - 1);
3512 
3513  /* Set auxiliary variables... */
3514  double latr = 0.5 * (met->lat[iy1] + met->lat[iy0]);
3515  double dx = 1000. * DEG2DX(met->lon[ix1] - met->lon[ix0], latr);
3516  double dy = 1000. * DEG2DY(met->lat[iy1] - met->lat[iy0]);
3517  double c0 = cos(met->lat[iy0] / 180. * M_PI);
3518  double c1 = cos(met->lat[iy1] / 180. * M_PI);
3519  double cr = cos(latr / 180. * M_PI);
3520  double vort = 2 * 7.2921e-5 * sin(latr * M_PI / 180.);
3521 
3522  /* Loop over grid points... */
3523  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
3524 
3525  /* Get gradients in longitude... */
3526  double dtdx
3527  = (met->t[ix1][iy][ip] - met->t[ix0][iy][ip]) * pows[ip] / dx;
3528  double dvdx = (met->v[ix1][iy][ip] - met->v[ix0][iy][ip]) / dx;
3529 
3530  /* Get gradients in latitude... */
3531  double dtdy
3532  = (met->t[ix][iy1][ip] - met->t[ix][iy0][ip]) * pows[ip] / dy;
3533  double dudy
3534  = (met->u[ix][iy1][ip] * c1 - met->u[ix][iy0][ip] * c0) / dy;
3535 
3536  /* Set indices... */
3537  int ip0 = GSL_MAX(ip - 1, 0);
3538  int ip1 = GSL_MIN(ip + 1, met->np - 1);
3539 
3540  /* Get gradients in pressure... */
3541  double dtdp, dudp, dvdp;
3542  double dp0 = 100. * (met->p[ip] - met->p[ip0]);
3543  double dp1 = 100. * (met->p[ip1] - met->p[ip]);
3544  if (ip != ip0 && ip != ip1) {
3545  double denom = dp0 * dp1 * (dp0 + dp1);
3546  dtdp = (dp0 * dp0 * met->t[ix][iy][ip1] * pows[ip1]
3547  - dp1 * dp1 * met->t[ix][iy][ip0] * pows[ip0]
3548  + (dp1 * dp1 - dp0 * dp0) * met->t[ix][iy][ip] * pows[ip])
3549  / denom;
3550  dudp = (dp0 * dp0 * met->u[ix][iy][ip1]
3551  - dp1 * dp1 * met->u[ix][iy][ip0]
3552  + (dp1 * dp1 - dp0 * dp0) * met->u[ix][iy][ip])
3553  / denom;
3554  dvdp = (dp0 * dp0 * met->v[ix][iy][ip1]
3555  - dp1 * dp1 * met->v[ix][iy][ip0]
3556  + (dp1 * dp1 - dp0 * dp0) * met->v[ix][iy][ip])
3557  / denom;
3558  } else {
3559  double denom = dp0 + dp1;
3560  dtdp =
3561  (met->t[ix][iy][ip1] * pows[ip1] -
3562  met->t[ix][iy][ip0] * pows[ip0]) / denom;
3563  dudp = (met->u[ix][iy][ip1] - met->u[ix][iy][ip0]) / denom;
3564  dvdp = (met->v[ix][iy][ip1] - met->v[ix][iy][ip0]) / denom;
3565  }
3566 
3567  /* Calculate PV... */
3568  met->pv[ix][iy][ip] = (float)
3569  (1e6 * G0 *
3570  (-dtdp * (dvdx - dudy / cr + vort) + dvdp * dtdx - dudp * dtdy));
3571  }
3572  }
3573  }
3574 
3575  /* Fix for polar regions... */
3576 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3577  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3578  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip++) {
3579  met->pv[ix][0][ip]
3580  = met->pv[ix][1][ip]
3581  = met->pv[ix][2][ip];
3582  met->pv[ix][met->ny - 1][ip]
3583  = met->pv[ix][met->ny - 2][ip]
3584  = met->pv[ix][met->ny - 3][ip];
3585  }
3586 }
3587 
3588 /*****************************************************************************/
3589 
3590 void read_met_sample(
3591  ctl_t * ctl,
3592  met_t * met) {
3593 
3594  met_t *help;
3595 
3596  /* Check parameters... */
3597  if (ctl->met_dp <= 1 && ctl->met_dx <= 1 && ctl->met_dy <= 1
3598  && ctl->met_sp <= 1 && ctl->met_sx <= 1 && ctl->met_sy <= 1)
3599  return;
3600 
3601  /* Set timer... */
3602  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_SAMPLE", NVTX_READ);
3603 
3604  /* Allocate... */
3605  ALLOC(help, met_t, 1);
3606 
3607  /* Copy data... */
3608  help->nx = met->nx;
3609  help->ny = met->ny;
3610  help->np = met->np;
3611  memcpy(help->lon, met->lon, sizeof(met->lon));
3612  memcpy(help->lat, met->lat, sizeof(met->lat));
3613  memcpy(help->p, met->p, sizeof(met->p));
3614 
3615  /* Smoothing... */
3616  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix += ctl->met_dx) {
3617  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy += ctl->met_dy) {
3618  for (int ip = 0; ip < met->np; ip += ctl->met_dp) {
3619  help->ps[ix][iy] = 0;
3620  help->zs[ix][iy] = 0;
3621  help->ts[ix][iy] = 0;
3622  help->us[ix][iy] = 0;
3623  help->vs[ix][iy] = 0;
3624  help->t[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3625  help->u[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3626  help->v[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3627  help->w[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3628  help->h2o[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3629  help->o3[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3630  help->lwc[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3631  help->iwc[ix][iy][ip] = 0;
3632  float wsum = 0;
3633  for (int ix2 = ix - ctl->met_sx + 1; ix2 <= ix + ctl->met_sx - 1;
3634  ix2++) {
3635  int ix3 = ix2;
3636  if (ix3 < 0)
3637  ix3 += met->nx;
3638  else if (ix3 >= met->nx)
3639  ix3 -= met->nx;
3640 
3641  for (int iy2 = GSL_MAX(iy - ctl->met_sy + 1, 0);
3642  iy2 <= GSL_MIN(iy + ctl->met_sy - 1, met->ny - 1); iy2++)
3643  for (int ip2 = GSL_MAX(ip - ctl->met_sp + 1, 0);
3644  ip2 <= GSL_MIN(ip + ctl->met_sp - 1, met->np - 1); ip2++) {
3645  float w = (1.0f - (float) abs(ix - ix2) / (float) ctl->met_sx)
3646  * (1.0f - (float) abs(iy - iy2) / (float) ctl->met_sy)
3647  * (1.0f - (float) abs(ip - ip2) / (float) ctl->met_sp);
3648  help->ps[ix][iy] += w * met->ps[ix3][iy2];
3649  help->zs[ix][iy] += w * met->zs[ix3][iy2];
3650  help->ts[ix][iy] += w * met->ts[ix3][iy2];
3651  help->us[ix][iy] += w * met->us[ix3][iy2];
3652  help->vs[ix][iy] += w * met->vs[ix3][iy2];
3653  help->t[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->t[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3654  help->u[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->u[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3655  help->v[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->v[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3656  help->w[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->w[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3657  help->h2o[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->h2o[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3658  help->o3[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->o3[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3659  help->lwc[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->lwc[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3660  help->iwc[ix][iy][ip] += w * met->iwc[ix3][iy2][ip2];
3661  wsum += w;
3662  }
3663  }
3664  help->ps[ix][iy] /= wsum;
3665  help->zs[ix][iy] /= wsum;
3666  help->ts[ix][iy] /= wsum;
3667  help->us[ix][iy] /= wsum;
3668  help->vs[ix][iy] /= wsum;
3669  help->t[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3670  help->u[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3671  help->v[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3672  help->w[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3673  help->h2o[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3674  help->o3[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3675  help->lwc[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3676  help->iwc[ix][iy][ip] /= wsum;
3677  }
3678  }
3679  }
3680 
3681  /* Downsampling... */
3682  met->nx = 0;
3683  for (int ix = 0; ix < help->nx; ix += ctl->met_dx) {
3684  met->lon[met->nx] = help->lon[ix];
3685  met->ny = 0;
3686  for (int iy = 0; iy < help->ny; iy += ctl->met_dy) {
3687  met->lat[met->ny] = help->lat[iy];
3688  met->ps[met->nx][met->ny] = help->ps[ix][iy];
3689  met->zs[met->nx][met->ny] = help->zs[ix][iy];
3690  met->ts[met->nx][met->ny] = help->ts[ix][iy];
3691  met->us[met->nx][met->ny] = help->us[ix][iy];
3692  met->vs[met->nx][met->ny] = help->vs[ix][iy];
3693  met->np = 0;
3694  for (int ip = 0; ip < help->np; ip += ctl->met_dp) {
3695  met->p[met->np] = help->p[ip];
3696  met->t[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->t[ix][iy][ip];
3697  met->u[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->u[ix][iy][ip];
3698  met->v[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->v[ix][iy][ip];
3699  met->w[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->w[ix][iy][ip];
3700  met->h2o[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->h2o[ix][iy][ip];
3701  met->o3[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->o3[ix][iy][ip];
3702  met->lwc[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->lwc[ix][iy][ip];
3703  met->iwc[met->nx][met->ny][met->np] = help->iwc[ix][iy][ip];
3704  met->np++;
3705  }
3706  met->ny++;
3707  }
3708  met->nx++;
3709  }
3710 
3711  /* Free... */
3712  free(help);
3713 }
3714 
3715 /*****************************************************************************/
3716 
3717 void read_met_surface(
3718  int ncid,
3719  met_t * met) {
3720 
3721  /* Set timer... */
3722  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_SURFACE", NVTX_READ);
3723 
3724  /* Read surface pressure... */
3725  if (!read_met_help_2d(ncid, "ps", "PS", met, met->ps, 0.01f, 1)) {
3726  if (!read_met_help_2d(ncid, "lnsp", "LNSP", met, met->ps, 1.0f, 1)) {
3727  ERRMSG("Cannot not read surface pressure data!");
3728  } else {
3729  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3730  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3731  met->ps[ix][iy] = (float) (exp(met->ps[ix][iy]) / 100.);
3732  }
3733  } else
3734  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3735  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3736  met->ps[ix][iy] = (float) met->p[0];
3737 
3738  /* Read geopotential height at the surface... */
3739  if (!read_met_help_2d
3740  (ncid, "z", "Z", met, met->zs, (float) (1. / (1000. * G0)), 1))
3741  if (!read_met_help_2d
3742  (ncid, "zm", "ZM", met, met->zs, (float) (1. / 1000.), 1))
3743  ERRMSG("Cannot read surface geopotential height!");
3744 
3745  /* Read temperature at the surface... */
3746  if (!read_met_help_2d(ncid, "t2m", "T2M", met, met->ts, 1.0, 1))
3747  WARN("Cannot read surface temperature!");
3748 
3749  /* Read zonal wind at the surface... */
3750  if (!read_met_help_2d(ncid, "u10m", "U10M", met, met->us, 1.0, 1))
3751  WARN("Cannot read surface zonal wind!");
3752 
3753  /* Read meridional wind at the surface... */
3754  if (!read_met_help_2d(ncid, "v10m", "V10M", met, met->vs, 1.0, 1))
3755  WARN("Cannot read surface meridional wind!");
3756 }
3757 
3758 /*****************************************************************************/
3759 
3760 void read_met_tropo(
3761  ctl_t * ctl,
3762  met_t * met) {
3763 
3764  double p2[200], pv[EP], pv2[200], t[EP], t2[200], th[EP],
3765  th2[200], z[EP], z2[200];
3766 
3767  /* Set timer... */
3768  SELECT_TIMER("READ_MET_TROPO", NVTX_READ);
3769 
3770  /* Get altitude and pressure profiles... */
3771 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3772  for (int iz = 0; iz < met->np; iz++)
3773  z[iz] = Z(met->p[iz]);
3774 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3775  for (int iz = 0; iz <= 190; iz++) {
3776  z2[iz] = 4.5 + 0.1 * iz;
3777  p2[iz] = P(z2[iz]);
3778  }
3779 
3780  /* Do not calculate tropopause... */
3781  if (ctl->met_tropo == 0)
3782 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3783  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3784  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3785  met->pt[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
3786 
3787  /* Use tropopause climatology... */
3788  else if (ctl->met_tropo == 1) {
3789 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3790  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3791  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++)
3792  met->pt[ix][iy] = (float) clim_tropo(met->time, met->lat[iy]);
3793  }
3794 
3795  /* Use cold point... */
3796  else if (ctl->met_tropo == 2) {
3797 
3798  /* Loop over grid points... */
3799 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(t,t2)
3800  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3801  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3802 
3803  /* Interpolate temperature profile... */
3804  for (int iz = 0; iz < met->np; iz++)
3805  t[iz] = met->t[ix][iy][iz];
3806  spline(z, t, met->np, z2, t2, 171);
3807 
3808  /* Find minimum... */
3809  int iz = (int) gsl_stats_min_index(t2, 1, 171);
3810  if (iz > 0 && iz < 170)
3811  met->pt[ix][iy] = (float) p2[iz];
3812  else
3813  met->pt[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
3814  }
3815  }
3816 
3817  /* Use WMO definition... */
3818  else if (ctl->met_tropo == 3 || ctl->met_tropo == 4) {
3819 
3820  /* Loop over grid points... */
3821 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(t,t2)
3822  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3823  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3824 
3825  /* Interpolate temperature profile... */
3826  int iz;
3827  for (iz = 0; iz < met->np; iz++)
3828  t[iz] = met->t[ix][iy][iz];
3829  spline(z, t, met->np, z2, t2, 191);
3830 
3831  /* Find 1st tropopause... */
3832  met->pt[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
3833  for (iz = 0; iz <= 170; iz++) {
3834  int found = 1;
3835  for (int iz2 = iz + 1; iz2 <= iz + 20; iz2++)
3836  if (LAPSE(p2[iz], t2[iz], p2[iz2], t2[iz2]) > 2.0) {
3837  found = 0;
3838  break;
3839  }
3840  if (found) {
3841  if (iz > 0 && iz < 170)
3842  met->pt[ix][iy] = (float) p2[iz];
3843  break;
3844  }
3845  }
3846 
3847  /* Find 2nd tropopause... */
3848  if (ctl->met_tropo == 4) {
3849  met->pt[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
3850  for (; iz <= 170; iz++) {
3851  int found = 1;
3852  for (int iz2 = iz + 1; iz2 <= iz + 10; iz2++)
3853  if (LAPSE(p2[iz], t2[iz], p2[iz2], t2[iz2]) < 3.0) {
3854  found = 0;
3855  break;
3856  }
3857  if (found)
3858  break;
3859  }
3860  for (; iz <= 170; iz++) {
3861  int found = 1;
3862  for (int iz2 = iz + 1; iz2 <= iz + 20; iz2++)
3863  if (LAPSE(p2[iz], t2[iz], p2[iz2], t2[iz2]) > 2.0) {
3864  found = 0;
3865  break;
3866  }
3867  if (found) {
3868  if (iz > 0 && iz < 170)
3869  met->pt[ix][iy] = (float) p2[iz];
3870  break;
3871  }
3872  }
3873  }
3874  }
3875  }
3876 
3877  /* Use dynamical tropopause... */
3878  else if (ctl->met_tropo == 5) {
3879 
3880  /* Loop over grid points... */
3881 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(pv,pv2,th,th2)
3882  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3883  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3884 
3885  /* Interpolate potential vorticity profile... */
3886  for (int iz = 0; iz < met->np; iz++)
3887  pv[iz] = met->pv[ix][iy][iz];
3888  spline(z, pv, met->np, z2, pv2, 171);
3889 
3890  /* Interpolate potential temperature profile... */
3891  for (int iz = 0; iz < met->np; iz++)
3892  th[iz] = THETA(met->p[iz], met->t[ix][iy][iz]);
3893  spline(z, th, met->np, z2, th2, 171);
3894 
3895  /* Find dynamical tropopause (3.5 PVU and 380 K)... */
3896  met->pt[ix][iy] = GSL_NAN;
3897  for (int iz = 0; iz <= 170; iz++)
3898  if (fabs(pv2[iz]) >= 3.5 || th2[iz] >= 380.) {
3899  if (iz > 0 && iz < 170)
3900  met->pt[ix][iy] = (float) p2[iz];
3901  break;
3902  }
3903  }
3904  }
3905 
3906  else
3907  ERRMSG("Cannot calculate tropopause!");
3908 
3909  /* Interpolate temperature, geopotential height, and water vapor vmr... */
3910 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared)
3911  for (int ix = 0; ix < met->nx; ix++)
3912  for (int iy = 0; iy < met->ny; iy++) {
3913  double h2ot, tt, zt;
3914  INTPOL_INIT;
3915  intpol_met_space_3d(met, met->t, met->pt[ix][iy], met->lon[ix],
3916  met->lat[iy], &tt, ci, cw, 1);
3917  intpol_met_space_3d(met, met->z, met->pt[ix][iy], met->lon[ix],
3918  met->lat[iy], &zt, ci, cw, 0);
3919  intpol_met_space_3d(met, met->h2o, met->pt[ix][iy], met->lon[ix],
3920  met->lat[iy], &h2ot, ci, cw, 0);
3921  met->tt[ix][iy] = (float) tt;
3922  met->zt[ix][iy] = (float) zt;
3923  met->h2ot[ix][iy] = (float) h2ot;
3924  }
3925 }

3927 /*****************************************************************************/
3928 
3929 double scan_ctl(
3930  const char *filename,
3931  int argc,
3932  char *argv[],
3933  const char *varname,
3934  int arridx,
3935  const char *defvalue,
3936  char *value) {
3937 
3938  FILE *in = NULL;
3939 
3940  char dummy[LEN], fullname1[LEN], fullname2[LEN], line[LEN],
3941  msg[2 * LEN], rvarname[LEN], rval[LEN];
3942 
3943  int contain = 0, i;
3944 
3945  /* Open file... */
3946  if (filename[strlen(filename) - 1] != '-')
3947  if (!(in = fopen(filename, "r")))
3948  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
3949 
3950  /* Set full variable name... */
3951  if (arridx >= 0) {
3952  sprintf(fullname1, "%s[%d]", varname, arridx);
3953  sprintf(fullname2, "%s[*]", varname);
3954  } else {
3955  sprintf(fullname1, "%s", varname);
3956  sprintf(fullname2, "%s", varname);
3957  }
3958 
3959  /* Read data... */
3960  if (in != NULL)
3961  while (fgets(line, LEN, in))
3962  if (sscanf(line, "%s %s %s", rvarname, dummy, rval) == 3)
3963  if (strcasecmp(rvarname, fullname1) == 0 ||
3964  strcasecmp(rvarname, fullname2) == 0) {
3965  contain = 1;
3966  break;
3967  }
3968  for (i = 1; i < argc - 1; i++)
3969  if (strcasecmp(argv[i], fullname1) == 0 ||
3970  strcasecmp(argv[i], fullname2) == 0) {
3971  sprintf(rval, "%s", argv[i + 1]);
3972  contain = 1;
3973  break;
3974  }
3975 
3976  /* Close file... */
3977  if (in != NULL)
3978  fclose(in);
3979 
3980  /* Check for missing variables... */
3981  if (!contain) {
3982  if (strlen(defvalue) > 0)
3983  sprintf(rval, "%s", defvalue);
3984  else {
3985  sprintf(msg, "Missing variable %s!\n", fullname1);
3986  ERRMSG(msg);
3987  }
3988  }
3989 
3990  /* Write info... */
3991  printf("%s = %s\n", fullname1, rval);
3992 
3993  /* Return values... */
3994  if (value != NULL)
3995  sprintf(value, "%s", rval);
3996  return atof(rval);
3997 }
3998 
3999 /*****************************************************************************/
4000 
4001 double sedi(
4002  double p,
4003  double T,
4004  double r_p,
4005  double rho_p) {
4006 
4007  double eta, G, K, lambda, rho, v;
4008 
4009  /* Convert units... */
4010  p *= 100.; /* from hPa to Pa */
4011  r_p *= 1e-6; /* from microns to m */
4012 
4013  /* Density of dry air... */
4014  rho = p / (RA * T);
4015 
4016  /* Dynamic viscosity of air... */
4017  eta = 1.8325e-5 * (416.16 / (T + 120.)) * pow(T / 296.16, 1.5);
4018 
4019  /* Thermal velocity of an air molecule... */
4020  v = sqrt(8. * KB * T / (M_PI * 4.8096e-26));
4021 
4022  /* Mean free path of an air molecule... */
4023  lambda = 2. * eta / (rho * v);
4024 
4025  /* Knudsen number for air... */
4026  K = lambda / r_p;
4027 
4028  /* Cunningham slip-flow correction... */
4029  G = 1. + K * (1.249 + 0.42 * exp(-0.87 / K));
4030 
4031  /* Sedimentation velocity... */
4032  return 2. * SQR(r_p) * (rho_p - rho) * G0 / (9. * eta) * G;
4033 }
4034 
4035 /*****************************************************************************/
4036 
4037 void spline(
4038  double *x,
4039  double *y,
4040  int n,
4041  double *x2,
4042  double *y2,
4043  int n2) {
4044 
4045  gsl_interp_accel *acc;
4046 
4047  gsl_spline *s;
4048 
4049  /* Allocate... */
4050  acc = gsl_interp_accel_alloc();
4051  s = gsl_spline_alloc(gsl_interp_cspline, (size_t) n);
4052 
4053  /* Interpolate profile... */
4054  gsl_spline_init(s, x, y, (size_t) n);
4055  for (int i = 0; i < n2; i++)
4056  if (x2[i] <= x[0])
4057  y2[i] = y[0];
4058  else if (x2[i] >= x[n - 1])
4059  y2[i] = y[n - 1];
4060  else
4061  y2[i] = gsl_spline_eval(s, x2[i], acc);
4062 
4063  /* Free... */
4064  gsl_spline_free(s);
4065  gsl_interp_accel_free(acc);
4066 }
4067 
4068 /*****************************************************************************/
4069 
4070 double stddev(
4071  double *data,
4072  int n) {
4073 
4074  if (n <= 0)
4075  return 0;
4076 
4077  double avg = 0, rms = 0;
4078 
4079  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
4080  avg += data[i];
4081  avg /= n;
4082 
4083  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
4084  rms += SQR(data[i] - avg);
4085 
4086  return sqrt(rms / (n - 1));
4087 }

4089 /*****************************************************************************/
4090 
4091 void time2jsec(
4092  int year,
4093  int mon,
4094  int day,
4095  int hour,
4096  int min,
4097  int sec,
4098  double remain,
4099  double *jsec) {
4100 
4101  struct tm t0, t1;
4102 
4103  t0.tm_year = 100;
4104  t0.tm_mon = 0;
4105  t0.tm_mday = 1;
4106  t0.tm_hour = 0;
4107  t0.tm_min = 0;
4108  t0.tm_sec = 0;
4109 
4110  t1.tm_year = year - 1900;
4111  t1.tm_mon = mon - 1;
4112  t1.tm_mday = day;
4113  t1.tm_hour = hour;
4114  t1.tm_min = min;
4115  t1.tm_sec = sec;
4116 
4117  *jsec = (double) timegm(&t1) - (double) timegm(&t0) + remain;
4118 }

4120 /*****************************************************************************/
4121 
4122 void timer(
4123  const char *name,
4124  int output) {
4125 
4126  static char namelist[NTIMER][100];
4127 
4128  static double runtime[NTIMER], t0, t1;
4129 
4130  static int it = -1, nt;
4131 
4132  /* Get time... */
4133  t1 = omp_get_wtime();
4134 
4135  /* Add elapsed timer to old timer... */
4136  if (it >= 0)
4137  runtime[it] += t1 - t0;
4138 
4139  /* Identify ID of new timer... */
4140  for (it = 0; it < nt; it++)
4141  if (strcasecmp(name, namelist[it]) == 0)
4142  break;
4143 
4144  /* Check whether this is a new timer... */
4145  if (it >= nt) {
4146  sprintf(namelist[it], "%s", name);
4147  if ((++nt) > NTIMER)
4148  ERRMSG("Too many timers!");
4149  }
4150 
4151  /* Save starting time... */
4152  t0 = t1;
4153 
4154  /* Report timers... */
4155  if (output) {
4156  for (int it2 = 0; it2 < nt; it2++)
4157  printf("TIMER_%s = %.3f s\n", namelist[it2], runtime[it2]);
4158  double total = 0.0;
4159  for (int it2 = 0; it2 < nt; it2++)
4160  total += runtime[it2];
4161  printf("TIMER_TOTAL = %.3f s\n", total);
4162  }
4163 }
