4165 /*****************************************************************************/
4166 
4167 void write_atm(
4168  const char *filename,
4169  ctl_t * ctl,
4170  atm_t * atm,
4171  double t) {
4172 
4173  FILE *in, *out;
4174 
4175  char line[LEN];
4176 
4177  double r, t0, t1;
4178 
4179  int ip, iq, year, mon, day, hour, min, sec;
4180 
4181  /* Set timer... */
4182  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_ATM", NVTX_WRITE);
4183 
4184  /* Set time interval for output... */
4185  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4186  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4187 
4188  /* Write info... */
4189  printf("Write atmospheric data: %s\n", filename);
4190 
4191  /* Write ASCII data... */
4192  if (ctl->atm_type == 0) {
4193 
4194  /* Check if gnuplot output is requested... */
4195  if (ctl->atm_gpfile[0] != '-') {
4196 
4197  /* Create gnuplot pipe... */
4198  if (!(out = popen("gnuplot", "w")))
4199  ERRMSG("Cannot create pipe to gnuplot!");
4200 
4201  /* Set plot filename... */
4202  fprintf(out, "set out \"%s.png\"\n", filename);
4203 
4204  /* Set time string... */
4205  jsec2time(t, &year, &mon, &day, &hour, &min, &sec, &r);
4206  fprintf(out, "timestr=\"%d-%02d-%02d, %02d:%02d UTC\"\n",
4207  year, mon, day, hour, min);
4208 
4209  /* Dump gnuplot file to pipe... */
4210  if (!(in = fopen(ctl->atm_gpfile, "r")))
4211  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
4212  while (fgets(line, LEN, in))
4213  fprintf(out, "%s", line);
4214  fclose(in);
4215  }
4216 
4217  else {
4218 
4219  /* Create file... */
4220  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4221  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4222  }
4223 
4224  /* Write header... */
4225  fprintf(out,
4226  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
4227  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
4228  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n" "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n");
4229  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
4230  fprintf(out, "# $%i = %s [%s]\n", iq + 5, ctl->qnt_name[iq],
4231  ctl->qnt_unit[iq]);
4232  fprintf(out, "\n");
4233 
4234  /* Write data... */
4235  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip += ctl->atm_stride) {
4236 
4237  /* Check time... */
4238  if (ctl->atm_filter && (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1))
4239  continue;
4240 
4241  /* Write output... */
4242  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g", atm->time[ip], Z(atm->p[ip]),
4243  atm->lon[ip], atm->lat[ip]);
4244  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
4245  fprintf(out, " ");
4246  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], atm->q[iq][ip]);
4247  }
4248  fprintf(out, "\n");
4249  }
4250 
4251  /* Close file... */
4252  fclose(out);
4253  }
4254 
4255  /* Write binary data... */
4256  else if (ctl->atm_type == 1) {
4257 
4258  /* Create file... */
4259  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4260  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4261 
4262  /* Write data... */
4263  FWRITE(&atm->np, int,
4264  1,
4265  out);
4266  FWRITE(atm->time, double,
4267  (size_t) atm->np,
4268  out);
4269  FWRITE(atm->p, double,
4270  (size_t) atm->np,
4271  out);
4272  FWRITE(atm->lon, double,
4273  (size_t) atm->np,
4274  out);
4275  FWRITE(atm->lat, double,
4276  (size_t) atm->np,
4277  out);
4278  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
4279  FWRITE(atm->q[iq], double,
4280  (size_t) atm->np,
4281  out);
4282 
4283  /* Close file... */
4284  fclose(out);
4285  }
4286 
4287  /* Error... */
4288  else
4289  ERRMSG("Atmospheric data type not supported!");
4290 }
4291 
4292 /*****************************************************************************/
4293 
4294 void write_csi(
4295  const char *filename,
4296  ctl_t * ctl,
4297  atm_t * atm,
4298  double t) {
4299 
4300  static FILE *in, *out;
4301 
4302  static char line[LEN];
4303 
4304  static double modmean[GX][GY][GZ], obsmean[GX][GY][GZ], rt, rt_old = -1e99,
4305  rz, rlon, rlat, robs, t0, t1, area[GY], dlon, dlat, dz, lat,
4306  x[1000000], y[1000000], work[2000000];
4307 
4308  static int obscount[GX][GY][GZ], ct, cx, cy, cz, ip, ix, iy, iz, n;
4309 
4310  /* Set timer... */
4311  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_CSI", NVTX_WRITE);
4312 
4313  /* Init... */
4314  if (t == ctl->t_start) {
4315 
4316  /* Check quantity index for mass... */
4317  if (ctl->qnt_m < 0)
4318  ERRMSG("Need quantity mass!");
4319 
4320  /* Open observation data file... */
4321  printf("Read CSI observation data: %s\n", ctl->csi_obsfile);
4322  if (!(in = fopen(ctl->csi_obsfile, "r")))
4323  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
4324 
4325  /* Create new file... */
4326  printf("Write CSI data: %s\n", filename);
4327  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4328  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4329 
4330  /* Write header... */
4331  fprintf(out,
4332  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
4333  "# $2 = number of hits (cx)\n"
4334  "# $3 = number of misses (cy)\n"
4335  "# $4 = number of false alarms (cz)\n"
4336  "# $5 = number of observations (cx + cy)\n"
4337  "# $6 = number of forecasts (cx + cz)\n"
4338  "# $7 = bias (ratio of forecasts and observations) [%%]\n"
4339  "# $8 = probability of detection (POD) [%%]\n"
4340  "# $9 = false alarm rate (FAR) [%%]\n"
4341  "# $10 = critical success index (CSI) [%%]\n");
4342  fprintf(out,
4343  "# $11 = hits associated with random chance\n"
4344  "# $12 = equitable threat score (ETS) [%%]\n"
4345  "# $13 = Pearson linear correlation coefficient\n"
4346  "# $14 = Spearman rank-order correlation coefficient\n"
4347  "# $15 = column density mean error (F - O) [kg/m^2]\n"
4348  "# $16 = column density root mean square error (RMSE) [kg/m^2]\n"
4349  "# $17 = column density mean absolute error [kg/m^2]\n"
4350  "# $18 = number of data points\n\n");
4351 
4352  /* Set grid box size... */
4353  dz = (ctl->csi_z1 - ctl->csi_z0) / ctl->csi_nz;
4354  dlon = (ctl->csi_lon1 - ctl->csi_lon0) / ctl->csi_nx;
4355  dlat = (ctl->csi_lat1 - ctl->csi_lat0) / ctl->csi_ny;
4356 
4357  /* Set horizontal coordinates... */
4358  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->csi_ny; iy++) {
4359  lat = ctl->csi_lat0 + dlat * (iy + 0.5);
4360  area[iy] = dlat * dlon * SQR(RE * M_PI / 180.) * cos(lat * M_PI / 180.);
4361  }
4362  }
4363 
4364  /* Set time interval... */
4365  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4366  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4367 
4368  /* Initialize grid cells... */
4369 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(ix,iy,iz)
4370  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->csi_nx; ix++)
4371  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->csi_ny; iy++)
4372  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->csi_nz; iz++)
4373  modmean[ix][iy][iz] = obsmean[ix][iy][iz] = obscount[ix][iy][iz] = 0;
4374 
4375  /* Read observation data... */
4376  while (fgets(line, LEN, in)) {
4377 
4378  /* Read data... */
4379  if (sscanf(line, "%lg %lg %lg %lg %lg", &rt, &rz, &rlon, &rlat, &robs) !=
4380  5)
4381  continue;
4382 
4383  /* Check time... */
4384  if (rt < t0)
4385  continue;
4386  if (rt > t1)
4387  break;
4388  if (rt < rt_old)
4389  ERRMSG("Time must be ascending!");
4390  rt_old = rt;
4391 
4392  /* Check observation data... */
4393  if (!isfinite(robs))
4394  continue;
4395 
4396  /* Calculate indices... */
4397  ix = (int) ((rlon - ctl->csi_lon0) / dlon);
4398  iy = (int) ((rlat - ctl->csi_lat0) / dlat);
4399  iz = (int) ((rz - ctl->csi_z0) / dz);
4400 
4401  /* Check indices... */
4402  if (ix < 0 || ix >= ctl->csi_nx ||
4403  iy < 0 || iy >= ctl->csi_ny || iz < 0 || iz >= ctl->csi_nz)
4404  continue;
4405 
4406  /* Get mean observation index... */
4407  obsmean[ix][iy][iz] += robs;
4408  obscount[ix][iy][iz]++;
4409  }
4410 
4411  /* Analyze model data... */
4412  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
4413 
4414  /* Check time... */
4415  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1)
4416  continue;
4417 
4418  /* Get indices... */
4419  ix = (int) ((atm->lon[ip] - ctl->csi_lon0) / dlon);
4420  iy = (int) ((atm->lat[ip] - ctl->csi_lat0) / dlat);
4421  iz = (int) ((Z(atm->p[ip]) - ctl->csi_z0) / dz);
4422 
4423  /* Check indices... */
4424  if (ix < 0 || ix >= ctl->csi_nx ||
4425  iy < 0 || iy >= ctl->csi_ny || iz < 0 || iz >= ctl->csi_nz)
4426  continue;
4427 
4428  /* Get total mass in grid cell... */
4429  modmean[ix][iy][iz] += atm->q[ctl->qnt_m][ip];
4430  }
4431 
4432  /* Analyze all grid cells... */
4433  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->csi_nx; ix++)
4434  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->csi_ny; iy++)
4435  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->csi_nz; iz++) {
4436 
4437  /* Calculate mean observation index... */
4438  if (obscount[ix][iy][iz] > 0)
4439  obsmean[ix][iy][iz] /= obscount[ix][iy][iz];
4440 
4441  /* Calculate column density... */
4442  if (modmean[ix][iy][iz] > 0)
4443  modmean[ix][iy][iz] /= (1e6 * area[iy]);
4444 
4445  /* Calculate CSI... */
4446  if (obscount[ix][iy][iz] > 0) {
4447  ct++;
4448  if (obsmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_obsmin &&
4449  modmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_modmin)
4450  cx++;
4451  else if (obsmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_obsmin &&
4452  modmean[ix][iy][iz] < ctl->csi_modmin)
4453  cy++;
4454  else if (obsmean[ix][iy][iz] < ctl->csi_obsmin &&
4455  modmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_modmin)
4456  cz++;
4457  }
4458 
4459  /* Save data for other verification statistics... */
4460  if (obscount[ix][iy][iz] > 0
4461  && (obsmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_obsmin
4462  || modmean[ix][iy][iz] >= ctl->csi_modmin)) {
4463  x[n] = modmean[ix][iy][iz];
4464  y[n] = obsmean[ix][iy][iz];
4465  if ((++n) > 1000000)
4466  ERRMSG("Too many data points to calculate statistics!");
4467  }
4468  }
4469 
4470  /* Write output... */
4471  if (fmod(t, ctl->csi_dt_out) == 0) {
4472 
4473  /* Calculate verification statistics
4474  (https://www.cawcr.gov.au/projects/verification/) ... */
4475  int nobs = cx + cy;
4476  int nfor = cx + cz;
4477  double bias = (nobs > 0) ? 100. * nfor / nobs : GSL_NAN;
4478  double pod = (nobs > 0) ? (100. * cx) / nobs : GSL_NAN;
4479  double far = (nfor > 0) ? (100. * cz) / nfor : GSL_NAN;
4480  double csi = (cx + cy + cz > 0) ? (100. * cx) / (cx + cy + cz) : GSL_NAN;
4481  double cx_rd = (ct > 0) ? (1. * nobs * nfor) / ct : GSL_NAN;
4482  double ets = (cx + cy + cz - cx_rd > 0) ?
4483  (100. * (cx - cx_rd)) / (cx + cy + cz - cx_rd) : GSL_NAN;
4484  double rho_p =
4485  (n > 0) ? gsl_stats_correlation(x, 1, y, 1, (size_t) n) : GSL_NAN;
4486  double rho_s =
4487  (n > 0) ? gsl_stats_spearman(x, 1, y, 1, (size_t) n, work) : GSL_NAN;
4488  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
4489  work[i] = x[i] - y[i];
4490  double mean = (n > 0) ? gsl_stats_mean(work, 1, (size_t) n) : GSL_NAN;
4491  double rmse = (n > 0) ? gsl_stats_sd_with_fixed_mean(work, 1, (size_t) n,
4492  0.0) : GSL_NAN;
4493  double absdev =
4494  (n > 0) ? gsl_stats_absdev_m(work, 1, (size_t) n, 0.0) : GSL_NAN;
4495 
4496  /* Write... */
4497  fprintf(out, "%.2f %d %d %d %d %d %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %d\n",
4498  t, cx, cy, cz, nobs, nfor, bias, pod, far, csi, cx_rd, ets,
4499  rho_p, rho_s, mean, rmse, absdev, n);
4500 
4501  /* Set counters to zero... */
4502  n = ct = cx = cy = cz = 0;
4503  }
4504 
4505  /* Close file... */
4506  if (t == ctl->t_stop)
4507  fclose(out);
4508 }
4509 
4510 /*****************************************************************************/
4511 
4512 void write_ens(
4513  const char *filename,
4514  ctl_t * ctl,
4515  atm_t * atm,
4516  double t) {
4517 
4518  static FILE *out;
4519 
4520  static double dummy, ens, lat, lon, p[NENS], q[NQ][NENS],
4521  t0, t1, x[NENS][3], xm[3];
4522 
4523  static int ip, iq;
4524 
4525  static size_t i, n;
4526 
4527  /* Set timer... */
4528  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_ENS", NVTX_WRITE);
4529 
4530  /* Init... */
4531  if (t == ctl->t_start) {
4532 
4533  /* Check quantities... */
4534  if (ctl->qnt_ens < 0)
4535  ERRMSG("Missing ensemble IDs!");
4536 
4537  /* Create new file... */
4538  printf("Write ensemble data: %s\n", filename);
4539  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4540  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4541 
4542  /* Write header... */
4543  fprintf(out,
4544  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
4545  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
4546  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n" "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n");
4547  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
4548  fprintf(out, "# $%d = %s (mean) [%s]\n", 5 + iq,
4549  ctl->qnt_name[iq], ctl->qnt_unit[iq]);
4550  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
4551  fprintf(out, "# $%d = %s (sigma) [%s]\n", 5 + ctl->nq + iq,
4552  ctl->qnt_name[iq], ctl->qnt_unit[iq]);
4553  fprintf(out, "# $%d = number of members\n\n", 5 + 2 * ctl->nq);
4554  }
4555 
4556  /* Set time interval... */
4557  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4558  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4559 
4560  /* Init... */
4561  ens = GSL_NAN;
4562  n = 0;
4563 
4564  /* Loop over air parcels... */
4565  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
4566 
4567  /* Check time... */
4568  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1)
4569  continue;
4570 
4571  /* Check ensemble id... */
4572  if (atm->q[ctl->qnt_ens][ip] != ens) {
4573 
4574  /* Write results... */
4575  if (n > 0) {
4576 
4577  /* Get mean position... */
4578  xm[0] = xm[1] = xm[2] = 0;
4579  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
4580  xm[0] += x[i][0] / (double) n;
4581  xm[1] += x[i][1] / (double) n;
4582  xm[2] += x[i][2] / (double) n;
4583  }
4584  cart2geo(xm, &dummy, &lon, &lat);
4585  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g", t, Z(gsl_stats_mean(p, 1, n)), lon,
4586  lat);
4587 
4588  /* Get quantity statistics... */
4589  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
4590  fprintf(out, " ");
4591  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], gsl_stats_mean(q[iq], 1, n));
4592  }
4593  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
4594  fprintf(out, " ");
4595  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], gsl_stats_sd(q[iq], 1, n));
4596  }
4597  fprintf(out, " %lu\n", n);
4598  }
4599 
4600  /* Init new ensemble... */
4601  ens = atm->q[ctl->qnt_ens][ip];
4602  n = 0;
4603  }
4604 
4605  /* Save data... */
4606  p[n] = atm->p[ip];
4607  geo2cart(0, atm->lon[ip], atm->lat[ip], x[n]);
4608  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
4609  q[iq][n] = atm->q[iq][ip];
4610  if ((++n) >= NENS)
4611  ERRMSG("Too many data points!");
4612  }
4613 
4614  /* Write results... */
4615  if (n > 0) {
4616 
4617  /* Get mean position... */
4618  xm[0] = xm[1] = xm[2] = 0;
4619  for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
4620  xm[0] += x[i][0] / (double) n;
4621  xm[1] += x[i][1] / (double) n;
4622  xm[2] += x[i][2] / (double) n;
4623  }
4624  cart2geo(xm, &dummy, &lon, &lat);
4625  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g", t, Z(gsl_stats_mean(p, 1, n)), lon, lat);
4626 
4627  /* Get quantity statistics... */
4628  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
4629  fprintf(out, " ");
4630  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], gsl_stats_mean(q[iq], 1, n));
4631  }
4632  for (iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
4633  fprintf(out, " ");
4634  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], gsl_stats_sd(q[iq], 1, n));
4635  }
4636  fprintf(out, " %lu\n", n);
4637  }
4638 
4639  /* Close file... */
4640  if (t == ctl->t_stop)
4641  fclose(out);
4642 }
4643 
4644 /*****************************************************************************/
4645 
4646 void write_grid(
4647  const char *filename,
4648  ctl_t * ctl,
4649  met_t * met0,
4650  met_t * met1,
4651  atm_t * atm,
4652  double t) {
4653 
4654  FILE *in, *out;
4655 
4656  char line[LEN];
4657 
4658  static double mass[GX][GY][GZ], vmr[GX][GY][GZ], vmr_expl, vmr_impl,
4659  z[GZ], dz, lon[GX], dlon, lat[GY], dlat, area[GY], rho_air,
4660  press[GZ], temp, cd, t0, t1, r;
4661 
4662  static int ip, ix, *ixs, iy, *iys, iz, *izs, np[GX][GY][GZ], year, mon, day,
4663  hour, min, sec;
4664 
4665  /* Set timer... */
4666  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_GRID", NVTX_WRITE);
4667 
4668  /* Check dimensions... */
4669  if (ctl->grid_nx > GX || ctl->grid_ny > GY || ctl->grid_nz > GZ)
4670  ERRMSG("Grid dimensions too large!");
4671 
4672  /* Set grid box size... */
4673  dz = (ctl->grid_z1 - ctl->grid_z0) / ctl->grid_nz;
4674  dlon = (ctl->grid_lon1 - ctl->grid_lon0) / ctl->grid_nx;
4675  dlat = (ctl->grid_lat1 - ctl->grid_lat0) / ctl->grid_ny;
4676 
4677  /* Set vertical coordinates... */
4678 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(iz)
4679  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->grid_nz; iz++) {
4680  z[iz] = ctl->grid_z0 + dz * (iz + 0.5);
4681  press[iz] = P(z[iz]);
4682  }
4683 
4684  /* Set horizontal coordinates... */
4685  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->grid_nx; ix++)
4686  lon[ix] = ctl->grid_lon0 + dlon * (ix + 0.5);
4687 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(iy)
4688  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->grid_ny; iy++) {
4689  lat[iy] = ctl->grid_lat0 + dlat * (iy + 0.5);
4690  area[iy] = dlat * dlon * SQR(RE * M_PI / 180.)
4691  * cos(lat[iy] * M_PI / 180.);
4692  }
4693 
4694  /* Set time interval for output... */
4695  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4696  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4697 
4698  /* Initialize grid... */
4699 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(ix,iy,iz)
4700  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->grid_nx; ix++)
4701  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->grid_ny; iy++)
4702  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->grid_nz; iz++) {
4703  mass[ix][iy][iz] = 0;
4704  vmr[ix][iy][iz] = 0;
4705  np[ix][iy][iz] = 0;
4706  }
4707 
4708  /* Allocate... */
4709  ALLOC(ixs, int,
4710  atm->np);
4711  ALLOC(iys, int,
4712  atm->np);
4713  ALLOC(izs, int,
4714  atm->np);
4715 
4716  /* Get indices... */
4717 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(ip)
4718  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
4719  ixs[ip] = (int) ((atm->lon[ip] - ctl->grid_lon0) / dlon);
4720  iys[ip] = (int) ((atm->lat[ip] - ctl->grid_lat0) / dlat);
4721  izs[ip] = (int) ((Z(atm->p[ip]) - ctl->grid_z0) / dz);
4722  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1
4723  || ixs[ip] < 0 || ixs[ip] >= ctl->grid_nx
4724  || iys[ip] < 0 || iys[ip] >= ctl->grid_ny
4725  || izs[ip] < 0 || izs[ip] >= ctl->grid_nz)
4726  izs[ip] = -1;
4727  }
4728 
4729  /* Average data... */
4730  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++)
4731  if (izs[ip] >= 0) {
4732  np[ixs[ip]][iys[ip]][izs[ip]]++;
4733  if (ctl->qnt_m >= 0)
4734  mass[ixs[ip]][iys[ip]][izs[ip]] += atm->q[ctl->qnt_m][ip];
4735  if (ctl->qnt_vmr >= 0)
4736  vmr[ixs[ip]][iys[ip]][izs[ip]] += atm->q[ctl->qnt_vmr][ip];
4737  }
4738 
4739  /* Free... */
4740  free(ixs);
4741  free(iys);
4742  free(izs);
4743 
4744  /* Check if gnuplot output is requested... */
4745  if (ctl->grid_gpfile[0] != '-') {
4746 
4747  /* Write info... */
4748  printf("Plot grid data: %s.png\n", filename);
4749 
4750  /* Create gnuplot pipe... */
4751  if (!(out = popen("gnuplot", "w")))
4752  ERRMSG("Cannot create pipe to gnuplot!");
4753 
4754  /* Set plot filename... */
4755  fprintf(out, "set out \"%s.png\"\n", filename);
4756 
4757  /* Set time string... */
4758  jsec2time(t, &year, &mon, &day, &hour, &min, &sec, &r);
4759  fprintf(out, "timestr=\"%d-%02d-%02d, %02d:%02d UTC\"\n",
4760  year, mon, day, hour, min);
4761 
4762  /* Dump gnuplot file to pipe... */
4763  if (!(in = fopen(ctl->grid_gpfile, "r")))
4764  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
4765  while (fgets(line, LEN, in))
4766  fprintf(out, "%s", line);
4767  fclose(in);
4768  }
4769 
4770  else {
4771 
4772  /* Write info... */
4773  printf("Write grid data: %s\n", filename);
4774 
4775  /* Create file... */
4776  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4777  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4778  }
4779 
4780  /* Write header... */
4781  fprintf(out,
4782  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
4783  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
4784  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n"
4785  "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n"
4786  "# $5 = surface area [km^2]\n"
4787  "# $6 = layer width [km]\n"
4788  "# $7 = number of particles [1]\n"
4789  "# $8 = column density (implicit) [kg/m^2]\n"
4790  "# $9 = volume mixing ratio (implicit) [ppv]\n"
4791  "# $10 = volume mixing ratio (explicit) [ppv]\n\n");
4792 
4793  /* Write data... */
4794  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->grid_nx; ix++) {
4795  if (ix > 0 && ctl->grid_ny > 1 && !ctl->grid_sparse)
4796  fprintf(out, "\n");
4797  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->grid_ny; iy++) {
4798  if (iy > 0 && ctl->grid_nz > 1 && !ctl->grid_sparse)
4799  fprintf(out, "\n");
4800  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->grid_nz; iz++)
4801  if (!ctl->grid_sparse || mass[ix][iy][iz] > 0 || vmr[ix][iy][iz] > 0) {
4802 
4803  /* Calculate column density... */
4804  if (ctl->qnt_m >= 0)
4805  cd = mass[ix][iy][iz] / (1e6 * area[iy]);
4806  else
4807  cd = GSL_NAN;
4808 
4809  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio (implicit)... */
4810  if (ctl->qnt_m >= 0 && ctl->molmass > 0) {
4811  vmr_impl = 0;
4812  if (mass[ix][iy][iz] > 0) {
4813 
4814  /* Get temperature... */
4815  INTPOL_INIT;
4816  intpol_met_time_3d(met0, met0->t, met1, met1->t, t, press[iz],
4817  lon[ix], lat[iy], &temp, ci, cw, 1);
4818 
4819  /* Calculate density of air... */
4820  rho_air = 100. * press[iz] / (RA * temp);
4821 
4822  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio... */
4823  vmr_impl = MA / ctl->molmass * mass[ix][iy][iz]
4824  / (rho_air * 1e6 * area[iy] * 1e3 * dz);
4825  }
4826  } else
4827  vmr_impl = GSL_NAN;
4828 
4829  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio (explicit)... */
4830  if (ctl->qnt_vmr >= 0 && np[ix][iy][iz] > 0)
4831  vmr_expl = vmr[ix][iy][iz] / np[ix][iy][iz];
4832  else
4833  vmr_expl = GSL_NAN;
4834 
4835  /* Write output... */
4836  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g %g %g %d %g %g %g\n", t, z[iz],
4837  lon[ix], lat[iy], area[iy], dz, np[ix][iy][iz], cd,
4838  vmr_impl, vmr_expl);
4839  }
4840  }
4841  }
4842 
4843  /* Close file... */
4844  fclose(out);
4845 }
4846 
4847 /*****************************************************************************/
4848 
4849 void write_prof(
4850  const char *filename,
4851  ctl_t * ctl,
4852  met_t * met0,
4853  met_t * met1,
4854  atm_t * atm,
4855  double t) {
4856 
4857  static FILE *in, *out;
4858 
4859  static char line[LEN];
4860 
4861  static double mass[GX][GY][GZ], obsmean[GX][GY], rt, rt_old = -1e99,
4862  rz, rlon, rlat, robs, t0, t1, area[GY], dz, dlon, dlat, lon[GX], lat[GY],
4863  z[GZ], press[GZ], temp, rho_air, vmr, h2o, o3;
4864 
4865  static int obscount[GX][GY], ip, ix, iy, iz, okay;
4866 
4867  /* Set timer... */
4868  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_PROF", NVTX_WRITE);
4869 
4870  /* Init... */
4871  if (t == ctl->t_start) {
4872 
4873  /* Check quantity index for mass... */
4874  if (ctl->qnt_m < 0)
4875  ERRMSG("Need quantity mass!");
4876 
4877  /* Check dimensions... */
4878  if (ctl->prof_nx > GX || ctl->prof_ny > GY || ctl->prof_nz > GZ)
4879  ERRMSG("Grid dimensions too large!");
4880 
4881  /* Check molar mass... */
4882  if (ctl->molmass <= 0)
4883  ERRMSG("Specify molar mass!");
4884 
4885  /* Open observation data file... */
4886  printf("Read profile observation data: %s\n", ctl->prof_obsfile);
4887  if (!(in = fopen(ctl->prof_obsfile, "r")))
4888  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
4889 
4890  /* Create new output file... */
4891  printf("Write profile data: %s\n", filename);
4892  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
4893  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
4894 
4895  /* Write header... */
4896  fprintf(out,
4897  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
4898  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
4899  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n"
4900  "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n"
4901  "# $5 = pressure [hPa]\n"
4902  "# $6 = temperature [K]\n"
4903  "# $7 = volume mixing ratio [ppv]\n"
4904  "# $8 = H2O volume mixing ratio [ppv]\n"
4905  "# $9 = O3 volume mixing ratio [ppv]\n"
4906  "# $10 = observed BT index [K]\n");
4907 
4908  /* Set grid box size... */
4909  dz = (ctl->prof_z1 - ctl->prof_z0) / ctl->prof_nz;
4910  dlon = (ctl->prof_lon1 - ctl->prof_lon0) / ctl->prof_nx;
4911  dlat = (ctl->prof_lat1 - ctl->prof_lat0) / ctl->prof_ny;
4912 
4913  /* Set vertical coordinates... */
4914  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->prof_nz; iz++) {
4915  z[iz] = ctl->prof_z0 + dz * (iz + 0.5);
4916  press[iz] = P(z[iz]);
4917  }
4918 
4919  /* Set horizontal coordinates... */
4920  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->prof_nx; ix++)
4921  lon[ix] = ctl->prof_lon0 + dlon * (ix + 0.5);
4922  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->prof_ny; iy++) {
4923  lat[iy] = ctl->prof_lat0 + dlat * (iy + 0.5);
4924  area[iy] = dlat * dlon * SQR(RE * M_PI / 180.)
4925  * cos(lat[iy] * M_PI / 180.);
4926  }
4927  }
4928 
4929  /* Set time interval... */
4930  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4931  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
4932 
4933  /* Initialize... */
4934 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) private(ix,iy,iz)
4935  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->prof_nx; ix++)
4936  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->prof_ny; iy++) {
4937  obsmean[ix][iy] = 0;
4938  obscount[ix][iy] = 0;
4939  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->prof_nz; iz++)
4940  mass[ix][iy][iz] = 0;
4941  }
4942 
4943  /* Read observation data... */
4944  while (fgets(line, LEN, in)) {
4945 
4946  /* Read data... */
4947  if (sscanf(line, "%lg %lg %lg %lg %lg", &rt, &rz, &rlon, &rlat, &robs) !=
4948  5)
4949  continue;
4950 
4951  /* Check time... */
4952  if (rt < t0)
4953  continue;
4954  if (rt > t1)
4955  break;
4956  if (rt < rt_old)
4957  ERRMSG("Time must be ascending!");
4958  rt_old = rt;
4959 
4960  /* Check observation data... */
4961  if (!isfinite(robs))
4962  continue;
4963 
4964  /* Calculate indices... */
4965  ix = (int) ((rlon - ctl->prof_lon0) / dlon);
4966  iy = (int) ((rlat - ctl->prof_lat0) / dlat);
4967 
4968  /* Check indices... */
4969  if (ix < 0 || ix >= ctl->prof_nx || iy < 0 || iy >= ctl->prof_ny)
4970  continue;
4971 
4972  /* Get mean observation index... */
4973  obsmean[ix][iy] += robs;
4974  obscount[ix][iy]++;
4975  }
4976 
4977  /* Analyze model data... */
4978  for (ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
4979 
4980  /* Check time... */
4981  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1)
4982  continue;
4983 
4984  /* Get indices... */
4985  ix = (int) ((atm->lon[ip] - ctl->prof_lon0) / dlon);
4986  iy = (int) ((atm->lat[ip] - ctl->prof_lat0) / dlat);
4987  iz = (int) ((Z(atm->p[ip]) - ctl->prof_z0) / dz);
4988 
4989  /* Check indices... */
4990  if (ix < 0 || ix >= ctl->prof_nx ||
4991  iy < 0 || iy >= ctl->prof_ny || iz < 0 || iz >= ctl->prof_nz)
4992  continue;
4993 
4994  /* Get total mass in grid cell... */
4995  mass[ix][iy][iz] += atm->q[ctl->qnt_m][ip];
4996  }
4997 
4998  /* Extract profiles... */
4999  for (ix = 0; ix < ctl->prof_nx; ix++)
5000  for (iy = 0; iy < ctl->prof_ny; iy++)
5001  if (obscount[ix][iy] > 0) {
5002 
5003  /* Check profile... */
5004  okay = 0;
5005  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->prof_nz; iz++)
5006  if (mass[ix][iy][iz] > 0) {
5007  okay = 1;
5008  break;
5009  }
5010  if (!okay)
5011  continue;
5012 
5013  /* Write output... */
5014  fprintf(out, "\n");
5015 
5016  /* Loop over altitudes... */
5017  for (iz = 0; iz < ctl->prof_nz; iz++) {
5018 
5019  /* Get pressure and temperature... */
5020  INTPOL_INIT;
5021  intpol_met_time_3d(met0, met0->t, met1, met1->t, t, press[iz],
5022  lon[ix], lat[iy], &temp, ci, cw, 1);
5023  intpol_met_time_3d(met0, met0->h2o, met1, met1->h2o, t, press[iz],
5024  lon[ix], lat[iy], &h2o, ci, cw, 0);
5025  intpol_met_time_3d(met0, met0->o3, met1, met1->o3, t, press[iz],
5026  lon[ix], lat[iy], &o3, ci, cw, 0);
5027 
5028  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio... */
5029  rho_air = 100. * press[iz] / (RA * temp);
5030  vmr = MA / ctl->molmass * mass[ix][iy][iz]
5031  / (rho_air * area[iy] * dz * 1e9);
5032 
5033  /* Write output... */
5034  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g %g\n",
5035  t, z[iz], lon[ix], lat[iy], press[iz], temp, vmr, h2o, o3,
5036  obsmean[ix][iy] / obscount[ix][iy]);
5037  }
5038  }
5039 
5040  /* Close files... */
5041  if (t == ctl->t_stop) {
5042  fclose(in);
5043  fclose(out);
5044  }
5045 }
5046 
5047 /*****************************************************************************/
5048 
5049 void write_sample(
5050  const char *filename,
5051  ctl_t * ctl,
5052  met_t * met0,
5053  met_t * met1,
5054  atm_t * atm,
5055  double t) {
5056 
5057  static FILE *in, *out;
5058 
5059  static char line[LEN];
5060 
5061  static double area, dlat, rmax2, t0, t1, rt, rt_old, rz, rlon, rlat, robs;
5062 
5063  /* Set timer... */
5064  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_SAMPLE", NVTX_WRITE);
5065 
5066  /* Init... */
5067  if (t == ctl->t_start) {
5068 
5069  /* Open observation data file... */
5070  printf("Read sample observation data: %s\n", ctl->sample_obsfile);
5071  if (!(in = fopen(ctl->sample_obsfile, "r")))
5072  ERRMSG("Cannot open file!");
5073 
5074  /* Create new file... */
5075  printf("Write sample data: %s\n", filename);
5076  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
5077  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
5078 
5079  /* Write header... */
5080  fprintf(out,
5081  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
5082  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
5083  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n"
5084  "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n"
5085  "# $5 = surface area [km^2]\n"
5086  "# $6 = layer width [km]\n"
5087  "# $7 = number of particles [1]\n"
5088  "# $8 = column density [kg/m^2]\n"
5089  "# $9 = volume mixing ratio [ppv]\n"
5090  "# $10 = observed BT index [K]\n\n");
5091 
5092  /* Set latitude range, squared radius, and area... */
5093  dlat = DY2DEG(ctl->sample_dx);
5094  rmax2 = SQR(ctl->sample_dx);
5095  area = M_PI * rmax2;
5096  }
5097 
5098  /* Set time interval for output... */
5099  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
5100  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
5101 
5102  /* Read observation data... */
5103  while (fgets(line, LEN, in)) {
5104 
5105  /* Read data... */
5106  if (sscanf(line, "%lg %lg %lg %lg %lg", &rt, &rz, &rlon, &rlat, &robs) !=
5107  5)
5108  continue;
5109 
5110  /* Check time... */
5111  if (rt < t0)
5112  continue;
5113  if (rt < rt_old)
5114  ERRMSG("Time must be ascending!");
5115  rt_old = rt;
5116 
5117  /* Calculate Cartesian coordinates... */
5118  double x0[3];
5119  geo2cart(0, rlon, rlat, x0);
5120 
5121  /* Set pressure range... */
5122  double rp = P(rz);
5123  double ptop = P(rz + ctl->sample_dz);
5124  double pbot = P(rz - ctl->sample_dz);
5125 
5126  /* Init... */
5127  double mass = 0;
5128  int np = 0;
5129 
5130  /* Loop over air parcels... */
5131 #pragma omp parallel for default(shared) reduction(+:mass,np)
5132  for (int ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
5133 
5134  /* Check time... */
5135  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1)
5136  continue;
5137 
5138  /* Check latitude... */
5139  if (fabs(rlat - atm->lat[ip]) > dlat)
5140  continue;
5141 
5142  /* Check horizontal distance... */
5143  double x1[3];
5144  geo2cart(0, atm->lon[ip], atm->lat[ip], x1);
5145  if (DIST2(x0, x1) > rmax2)
5146  continue;
5147 
5148  /* Check pressure... */
5149  if (ctl->sample_dz > 0)
5150  if (atm->p[ip] > pbot || atm->p[ip] < ptop)
5151  continue;
5152 
5153  /* Add mass... */
5154  if (ctl->qnt_m >= 0)
5155  mass += atm->q[ctl->qnt_m][ip];
5156  np++;
5157  }
5158 
5159  /* Calculate column density... */
5160  double cd = mass / (1e6 * area);
5161 
5162  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio... */
5163  double vmr = 0;
5164  if (ctl->molmass > 0 && ctl->sample_dz > 0) {
5165  if (mass > 0) {
5166 
5167  /* Get temperature... */
5168  double temp;
5169  INTPOL_INIT;
5170  intpol_met_time_3d(met0, met0->t, met1, met1->t, rt, rp,
5171  rlon, rlat, &temp, ci, cw, 1);
5172 
5173  /* Calculate density of air... */
5174  double rho_air = 100. * rp / (RA * temp);
5175 
5176  /* Calculate volume mixing ratio... */
5177  vmr = MA / ctl->molmass * mass
5178  / (rho_air * 1e6 * area * 1e3 * ctl->sample_dz);
5179  }
5180  } else
5181  vmr = GSL_NAN;
5182 
5183  /* Write output... */
5184  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g %g %g %d %g %g %g\n", rt, rz, rlon, rlat,
5185  area, ctl->sample_dz, np, cd, vmr, robs);
5186 
5187  /* Check time... */
5188  if (rt >= t1)
5189  break;
5190  }
5191 
5192  /* Close files... */
5193  if (t == ctl->t_stop) {
5194  fclose(in);
5195  fclose(out);
5196  }
5197 }

5199 /*****************************************************************************/
5200 
5201 void write_station(
5202  const char *filename,
5203  ctl_t * ctl,
5204  atm_t * atm,
5205  double t) {
5206 
5207  static FILE *out;
5208 
5209  static double rmax2, t0, t1, x0[3], x1[3];
5210 
5211  /* Set timer... */
5212  SELECT_TIMER("WRITE_STATION", NVTX_WRITE);
5213 
5214  /* Init... */
5215  if (t == ctl->t_start) {
5216 
5217  /* Write info... */
5218  printf("Write station data: %s\n", filename);
5219 
5220  /* Create new file... */
5221  if (!(out = fopen(filename, "w")))
5222  ERRMSG("Cannot create file!");
5223 
5224  /* Write header... */
5225  fprintf(out,
5226  "# $1 = time [s]\n"
5227  "# $2 = altitude [km]\n"
5228  "# $3 = longitude [deg]\n" "# $4 = latitude [deg]\n");
5229  for (int iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++)
5230  fprintf(out, "# $%i = %s [%s]\n", (iq + 5),
5231  ctl->qnt_name[iq], ctl->qnt_unit[iq]);
5232  fprintf(out, "\n");
5233 
5234  /* Set geolocation and search radius... */
5235  geo2cart(0, ctl->stat_lon, ctl->stat_lat, x0);
5236  rmax2 = SQR(ctl->stat_r);
5237  }
5238 
5239  /* Set time interval for output... */
5240  t0 = t - 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
5241  t1 = t + 0.5 * ctl->dt_mod;
5242 
5243  /* Loop over air parcels... */
5244  for (int ip = 0; ip < atm->np; ip++) {
5245 
5246  /* Check time... */
5247  if (atm->time[ip] < t0 || atm->time[ip] > t1)
5248  continue;
5249 
5250  /* Check station flag... */
5251  if (ctl->qnt_stat >= 0)
5252  if (atm->q[ctl->qnt_stat][ip])
5253  continue;
5254 
5255  /* Get Cartesian coordinates... */
5256  geo2cart(0, atm->lon[ip], atm->lat[ip], x1);
5257 
5258  /* Check horizontal distance... */
5259  if (DIST2(x0, x1) > rmax2)
5260  continue;
5261 
5262  /* Set station flag... */
5263  if (ctl->qnt_stat >= 0)
5264  atm->q[ctl->qnt_stat][ip] = 1;
5265 
5266  /* Write data... */
5267  fprintf(out, "%.2f %g %g %g",
5268  atm->time[ip], Z(atm->p[ip]), atm->lon[ip], atm->lat[ip]);
5269  for (int iq = 0; iq < ctl->nq; iq++) {
5270  fprintf(out, " ");
5271  fprintf(out, ctl->qnt_format[iq], atm->q[iq][ip]);
5272  }
5273  fprintf(out, "\n");
5274  }
5275 
5276  /* Close file... */
5277  if (t == ctl->t_stop)
5278  fclose(out);
5279 }
